The Ayleid King opened a portal to the Hollow City. I should follow him and travel there.
I'm back in the Hollow City. I should locate King Laloriaran Dynar and make sure he arrived safely.
Skordo should be waiting by the passage to the upper level. I could talk to him or just head right upstairs now that I have the key.
Ezreba was there when Halindor's wife Bowenas was taken. Halindor doesn't know where Bowenas was taken, but Ezreba's home is a good place to start looking.

Azum told me that she's not supposed to talk about guests at the caravan, but the games-runners might not be so tight-lipped. Dulan, Khaba, and Bunul were the games-runners she called out as being my best bets. I should seek one of them out.
The game dealer at the Lizard Races told me that he saw <<1>>, and that he got into a drunken brawl. I should ask some of the other dealers if they saw anything.
The game dealer at the troll fighting arena said that <<1>> lost all his gold and tried to borrow more. When he became belligerent, she reported his outburst to <<2>>. I should talk to <<3>> again.
The spikeball game dealer told me that he saw <<1>>'s men chasing <<2>>. I should talk to another dealer.
I should to bet on the lizard races. The dealer there might know more about <<1>>'s whereabouts.
I should to bet on the troll fights. The dealer there might know more about <<1>>'s whereabouts.
I should compete in Spikeball. The dealer there might know more about <<1>>'s whereabouts.

After talking to the game dealers, it appears that <<1>> lost all of his gold and tried to borrow more. When he became belligerent, his outburst was reported to <<2>>, the games manager. I should talk to <<2>> again.

After talking to the game dealers, it appears that <<1>> lost all of his gold and tried to borrow more. When he became belligerent, his outburst was reported to <<2>>, the games manager. I should talk to <<2>> again.
Bowenas has been trapped in one of these strange rituals inside Ezreba's home. I need to destroy the crystal to free her.
Bowenas is free of the ritual. I should talk to her and see if I can get to the bottom of this.
Bowenas said that Ezreba had gone to the ruined temple, which is exactly what Halindor said to me. I need to search the temple to see if I can find either of them.
Near where I saw the second vision, there's an old journal lying on the ground. It might contain more details about what happened here.
I should meet <<1>>'s regiment on the outskirts of the Daedric ruin.
The Aspect of Namira is here, along with some Dremora in strange-looking magical bubbles. I should confront her.
I'm to meet <<1>> at <<2>>. She believes an Argonian keeper will know more about <<A:3>>.
I've found a trapdoor at the back of the temple ruins. Perhaps this is where Ezreba went?
I've found Halindor looking fairly stunned on the ground in the Catacombs. I should speak to him.
I've stumbled on a dark ritual being enacted. It seems as though this is where the dark energy beings originate. I should stop the ritual.
I have the Overseer's key. I should use it to head up to the next level of the Tower of Lies.
While Skordo musters his soldiers, I've made my way to the upper level of the prison to find Captain Eilram.
Captain Eilram won't work with me until I convince him that I'm not a spy or an illusion. He wants me to recover the sword that he dropped while fighting the ogrims.
I recovered Captain Eilram's dagger. I should return it to him to prove that he can trust me.

Eilram and Arakh both seem to be suffering from the terrible effects of this place. I recovered Eilram's sword, so maybe he'll trust me now. I should meet him near Arakh's camp and see if I can help him talk some sense into the other captain.
I should find Captain Eilram and give his sword.
Captain Arakh is more paranoid than Captain Eilram. She says the voices are making her crazy. She won't even talk to Eilram until someone recovers her helmet from the watchers. I guess I'm elected.
I recovered Captain Arakh's helmet from the watchers. I should return it to her and see if it calms her down enough so that Eilram can talk to her.
The helmet seems to have calmed Captain Arakh. Now Captain Eilram wants to talk to her. I should listen to what they have to say.
The Dremora Lyranth appeared. She claims that we have a common enemy in Ifriz. I should talk to her and see what she has to say.

A Dremora named Ifriz seems to be in charge of this prison. According to Lyranth, the only way to remove the barrier blocking the exit is to kill Ifriz. Of course, she wants him dead, too. She banished the illusions that had been hiding him.
There's another journal lying on the ground near Endarre's bones. Perhaps it will contain clues as to how to continue through the dungeon.
Ezreba is somewhere here in the catacombs. I need to find and talk to her.
I should return to and speak to Unishi.
I should talk to the Groundskeeper to learn more about the Hollow City.
I should speak to the Groundskeeper and see if she has a suggestion on how I should proceed.
<<1>> arrived with reinforcement. They should be able to clear out the remaining Dominion forces. Perhaps she knows where the Dominion took <<A:2>>.
I should help <<1>> buy time until <<2>> returns with reinforcements to drive out the Dominion.
<<1>> asked me to light braziers at the top of two Xanmeers, as well as find <<2>>. I should listen for what the Dominion might be plotting.
I lit the braziers and found <<1>>. I should return to <<2>> and share what I've learned of the Dominion's plans.
<<1>> began the hatching ritual. I should stay alert for Dominion activity until he finishes.
The hatching ritual went horribly wrong. <<1>>'s assistant Ahaht-Ei died during the ritual, and he looks to be in severe pain. I should find out what happened.
<<1>> sacrificed himself to Sithis, buying us time to save the remaining eggs from the Dominion. I should move before the Dominion has a chance to destroy them all.
The keepers' assistants gave their lives to protect the eggs. With their help, I was able to save several. I should return them to <<1>>.
I arrived at the Harborage and should speak with the Prophet.
The Prophet has summoned me to the Harborage. I should go there at once.
The Prophet has opened the way to Coldharbour and the Castle of the Worm. It is time to set out.
Lyris wants to have a word with me.
We need to find a way into the Castle of the Worm. Lyris suggested we find someone who can help.
I can talk to slaves in the town to get information on how to enter the castle safely.
I should make my way up into the keep.
I've entered the castle dungeons. I need to make my way up into the keep.
I've entered the central keep. I should search around for any clues.
I should follow up with Lyris about what I've found.
It appears that Abnur Tharn is in the castle somewhere. I should keep an eye out for him as I search for my soul.
Abnur Tharn's projection is here. I should speak to him.
A magical barrier prevents me from moving forward. A Daedra has offered to sunder the barrier for me in exchange for putting his soul into a flesh atronach, so that he is spared discorporation.
I need to get to Abnur Tharn before the Worm Cult catches on.
Abnur Tharn is nearby. I should speak with him.
Mannimarco has arrived to stop Abnur Tharn from giving me more information. I must defeat the necromancer.
Abnur Tharn clawed his way out of the pit of darkness and his magic allowed me to strike down Mannimarco's projected form. I should speak to Abnur again.
We must escape the castle before Mannimarco can reform and set his entire castle guard upon us.
Abnur, Lyris, and I have dropped down into the effluvia below the tower summit. We must swim out.
We have fallen into the castle cistern. We can escape from here.
We fell into a pit beneath the castle. The Prophet should be waiting for us.
We reached the Prophet's portal. I should return to the Harborage.
I learned that the Prophet is actually Varen Aquilarios. He and I need to have words.
I need to finish talking to Varen Aquilarios in the Harborage.
I completed the Trial of Body. Now I should speak to <<1>> and start the Trial of Spirit.
I completed the Trial of Spirit. I should return to <<1>> and let her know about my success.
The Trial of Body requires that I enter the north pyramid and find the Dremora who collect and process the sap that comes from the Hist tree.
To find Pelidil's location, I must confront Asteril, the Thalmor officer who was spying on Pelidil's behalf. I need to speak to Oromin about accompanying me to the Thalmor Residence.
To find Pelidil's location, I must confront Asteril, the Thalmor officer who was spying on Pelidil's behalf. I should search for Asteril at the Thalmor Residence.
It appears as if Pelidil's spy within the Thalmor has been killed. I should examine the body for clues.
Inexplicably, it appears as if Pelidil's spy, Asteril, has been dead for some time. I should speak with Oromin.
Razum-dar found a hidden passage in the Thalmor Residence leading to the Old Imperial Underground. I should investigate.
I can now channel Limpaz's soul into the atronach. I need merely invoke the ritual from the book on the pedestal.
Beneath the Thalmor Residence, I found a small room that's connected to the Old Imperial Underground. I should look for clues to explain what's going on.

A letter from Pelidil suggests Asteril's sister, Laryaril, was the one who attempted to assassinate Razum-dar when he was disguised as the queen. Laryaril is to meet Pelidil in the Old Imperial Prison. I should go there to confront them.

A letter from Pelidil suggests Asteril's sister, Laryaril, was the one who attempted to assassinate Razum-dar when he was disguised as the queen. Laryaril is to meet Pelidil in the Old Imperial Prison. I need to find them and confront them.

Laryaril revealed that Pelidil has signed a treaty with the Maormer and plans to attack Seaside Sanctuary. He's also planning to raise Prince Naemon to lead an undead army. I should return to Woodhearth and tell Treethane Fariel what I learned.
I should follow Ezreba and question her.
I need to follow the Groundskeeper around the Hollow City and listen to the story she wants to tell me.
I need to follow the Groundskeeper around the Hollow City and listen to the story she wants to tell me.
I need to follow the Groundskeeper around the Hollow City and listen to the story she wants to tell me.
I need to follow the Groundskeeper around the Hollow City and listen to the story she wants to tell me.
I need to follow the Groundskeeper around the Hollow City and listen to the story she wants to tell me.
Sees-All-Colors said the appearance of the Ayleid spirits may be of some importance. I should witness what happens.
Valasha's journal is still intact. Sees-All-Colors believes it may have information we need on our mission.
I defeated the Servant of Naemon and escaped from the Shadow Wood. I should speak to Indaenir.
I've convinced the warden that I have captured Lyris Titanborn. We should be able to sneak through the dungeons safely, as long as I don't blow our cover.
The Groundskeeper seems to be finished giving me a tour of the Hollow City. I should speak to her.
Ifriz the Unraveler is dead and the barrier blocking the way out should be down now. I should meet the Fighters Guild captains at the bridge and make sure we can get out of here now.
I need to follow the Groundskeeper around the Hollow City and listen to the story she wants to tell me.

King Laloriaran Dynar is imprisoned to the west, beyond the Moonless Walk. Vanus Galerion is trapped somewhere to the east. I should also watch for any of the other missing Fighters Guild and Mages Guild members, or anyone else who can help me.

Telenger the Artificer discovered a portal inside the library vault. There's something powerful and potentially useful on the other side. Telenger has unlocked the vault and asked me to join him inside.
I entered the vault. I should talk to Telenger and see what he wants to do next.
I came across a pedestal that holds a bright crystal of light. I think Telenger was right. I think that is one of the fabled Lights of Meridia.
I stepped through the library vault portal and find myself on a floating rock high above the Library of Dusk. I should investigate the area and find the source of the power Telenger detected.

Telenger the Artificer doesn't trust himself due to the Daedric spell that continues to asault his mind. He wants me to enter the portal and find the source of the power he detected on the other side.
I obtained the Light of Meridia and need to get back to the surface. An image of King Laloriaran Dynar appeared before me and said that he will protect me if I choose to jump off the floating rock.

Lyris has asked me to manipulate the devices on either side of the Prophet's Cell.

The Prophet knows of a Daedric Anchor we can use to return to Tamriel. We should leave this place.

Without further ado, it is my great honor to presentâ€¦ a magically corrupted strain of Shalk. I call themâ€¦ Incineration Beetles!
What a night! I can't believe what's going on around here. Soldiers all over.
This is the Companions' fault. Never liked them hanging around town like that anyway.
I don't know about that, but the Reachmen sure want something in that mine.
Well, how do you like being part of the Pact now? They cleaned things up, eh?
What? Town's a mess, Sinmur's back, Fallowstone's overrun. Don't need friends like that.
Come on, the Pact helped us out of a jam. I'm happy to have allies like that.
Sergeant Aera was a Worm Cultist!
I don't believe it. Fjora said Aera saved her life. She's a hero!
Someone saw Aera run into the crypt.
So what? I bet she was chasing Worm Cultists, killing the last of them.
You're heading to Lost Prospect? Skip it.
Why?
Nobody who goes there ever comes back. It's crawling with zombies.
Bah, just rumors. If that was true, the Watch'd take care of it.
The Watch has bigger problems. Like that giant. I'd avoid Lost Prospect, if I was you.
You heard about Lost Prospect? I told you!
You told me what?
Viveka just got back from there. Killed a lich and lots of zombies!
Shor's Blood! What happened? How did she survive?
One of Jorunn's soldiers saved her. Killed the lich and the zombies too. Damn fine work!
It is a trap!
Aye, it's safer here, but I miss Fullhelm. And that hardass Ironhand.
What about old Wandering Eye?
Ha! Thorulf was an odd duck for sure. He'd stare out that window for hours.
Ugh! Creepy. And the way he looked at Mistress Hallfrida was just, well â€¦ obscene.
Don't worry about Hallfrida. Any man lays a hand on her will get a dagger in his belly.
Guldir! Wait 'til you hear. Thorulf was with the Worm Cult!
No! You're not serious. Is he dead?
He got away. Tricked the Thane into trying to kill himself. Old Ironhand's still alive, though.
Thank Dibella! How was he saved?
The Skald King's bodyguard saved Ironhand and the whole fort, from an army of undead no less!
Guldir! Wait 'til you hear. Thorulf was with the Worm Cult!
No! Old Wandering Eye? Did they kill him?
The Thane's bodyguard got him. Bless them for that. But Old Ironhand's dead.
No! What happened?
Thorulf tricked him into burning himself alive. Hallfrida's Thane now. If not for that bodyguard, they'd all be dead.
Where are the Three when you need them most? Nowhere!
Keep your voice down, Belera. The Hands of Almalexia don't tolerate blasphemy.
But we have to tolerate indifference? Where's the justice in that?
I heard the Reachmen are up in the mountains, and maybe at Fallowstone Hall too
Really? Then why is Vigrod here? Shouldn't he be at the Hall?
No idea. It's just a rumor. Like the one about Reachmen with trained bears up in the mountains.
Did you hear about Fallowstone Hall? Vigrod and someone from the Pact took it back!
That's a relief. Don't know why Vigrod left the Hall in the first place.
He's always looked after Shor's. Knowing Vigrod, he's taking the losses at the Hall pretty hard.
This looks promising. Let's start searching!
Wicked thieves! This one fairly stole these gems!
The lovely elf-woman will be unable to resist me now!
We can't let him get away!
You are as slow as you are ugly!
We have to catch him!
You first!
Follow if you dare, tiny elf-man!
He's gone through the gate! Hurry!
Eat the beans! The beans!
No! I mustn't! Y'ffre, protect me from these loathsome legumes!
These challengers are surpisingly fierce! But here's the real reason you've come today!
I give you the most dangerous creature the wastes of Alik'r have ever spawned!
Thank you. Had I eaten that mess, I wouldn't have broken the Pact, but they surely would have killed me.
Prepare yourself, combatants! Pray to your gods and make your peace. You face the Stinger!
What? Impossible? How did you win?
Stop the vestige at all costs! Soldiers, fall in!
target: Fermate il vestigio ad ogni costo! Soldati, schieratevi!

source: Please, help me!
From the volcanic island of Vvardenfell. A creature of fury that knows no mercy. The vicious â€¦ the cruel â€¦ the Troll King!
The door is there, to the west.
I can't believe all this horrible talk about the Maulborn.
They do seem to be completely devoted to their cause.
Yes, but their cause is evil! What don't you understand about that?
The price you're asking is outrageous.
Don't want to pay? That's fine, I'm sure I can find someone who'll meet my price over in Skywatch.
The Green take you. I won't have those upland upstarts outselling me. Your price is met.
This way!
So what do your people value? I'm thinking of seeking trading partners in Vulkwasten.
Well. Don't bother with booze. Most Bosmer don't imbibe. Meat. They always need more meat.
I sunk some coin into a farm a few years back. I'll have to speak with my man in Greenwater.
The quality of the steel from Mathiisen is excellent. Have you seen the blades they're making up there?
Oh yes. I've got an in with the foreman. Getting some for a great price.
Bah. Damn you tallies and your nepotism. I need a stepstool to get a fair deal around here.
You no take mammoth!
I say, did you see that Khajiit scum near the temple grounds? Disgusting, letting a mongrel near the house of Auri-El.
I quite agree. Too bad they put in the hunting ban. Our fathers had quite the time, eh?
Just so! And well put, sir, well put.
The stink. That's the worst part.
You know what, you're right. At first I thought those nasty little teeth were the worst part. But the smell! Ugh.
Comes of eating all that meat. What normal folk could stomach - ugh. What normal folk could stomach a meat drink?
Why would you ever go to that horrible little backwater?
I'm telling you, the beasts of Shattered Grove come right up to you. Bears eat right out of your hand!
Amazing. Can't wait to try out the blade father gave me. Good Mathiisen steel against bearflesh!
I would sooner die than harm Y'ffre's blessed wood!
You will chop this tree or die!
Please, you must stop these bastards. They spoke of raising an Ehlnofey.
They hope to shatter Y'ffre's Blessing! Please, you must stop them!
Lyris, child. Are you all right?
Yes, Prophet. I'm fine. The Vestige freed my mind from the Daedra's control.
Thank the Divines. Your loss would have thrown all into chaos.
They won't take me again. Not alive, at least.
Sorry, but I can't be caught or killed. Good luck!
Take up the torch and burn the tree!
I will protect the Green with my life! I will not break the Pact!
There! Get them!
About time! Help me kill this one and let's get out of here!
Was he there, child? Was Mannimarco present at the Castle?
No, the runt wasn't there from what I could tell. Then again, I was just guarding the door.
That is good. We are not ready for such a confrontation. The King of Worms would have destroyed you both.
You're playing this too cautiously, sir. Should've brought in a trebuchet with us.
You know very well that is not in my power. Rest now, Lyris. Let me see to your wounds.
Stop! You twoâ€”hold it right there!
The Reachmen talked of an ancient tomb down here, something about the Companions.
I heard the shamans talk of "Sinmur," some ancient creature, evil I'd guess.
I need to get out of here. Those shamans are looking for some long-dead monster!
Get out of here, mage! You're ruining the play. The villains are about to take the stage.
The shamans found a tomb deep in the mine. I'm not staying around to see what they're up to!
Dark powers gather ahead.
Reach shamans seek Sinmur, an ancient foe of the Companions.
I sense the spirit of Sinmur drawing near!
If Sinmur walks again, death and devastation will stalk the land!
We have a challenger! Let's welcome them to the party!
Who dares disturb the rest of <<1>>?
What is this, amateur hour? Begone, mage!
Awaken, thralls! Destroy these tomb robbers!
I am <<1>>! Meet your doom!
Stupid mage. He's trying to upstage you! Time to bring down the house. Break a leg. And a covenant.
Fitting, only the gods can save you now!
I'm getting out of here!
They've taken Tovisa and the rest into the mine!
Just a little bit further.
Not one step further! For the Empire!
It will be over soon.
I can help.
No, don't!
Damn! Discovered!
Now we'll see what the Mad God has in store. Be brave, adept.
Ha ha!
Ho, friend!
After you.
I am an Oathbreaker, you fool! Did you think the Cult would not have a plan? Dringoth will rise, and soon your corpse will join us.
No! No hit in face! Byz sweep!
By the Three, we will rebuild, dear. We will rebuild.
The Dominion took everything from us. I'll kill them. I'll kill them all.
I'll kill them. I'll kill them all.
Get away from here! I don't want to be let out!
Mother! You left me â€¦. I'm all alone.
The other students, the other mages, they all hate me.
You were the only one â€¦.
And now you're gone.
You didn't come home last night. I waited all night for you. Have you been working this entire time?
Shalidor! Eyevea is lost â€¦ you're obsessed! Can you even hear me?
I can't do this anymore. You love your spells and scrolls more than you love me. I'm leaving you. Can you hear me now?
Goodbye â€¦ you stupid old fool.
Ulfie â€¦ my love? I swear I just heard you. Where did you go?
Let's see here â€¦.
It works! I knew it would, of course.
Into the tunnel you go. Now to get that door open!
At long lastâ€”Bthzark! Come, we'll talk of our next move inside.
A happy side effect of restoring the power is that I can get this door open for you. There! That should do it!
These writings could prove crucial to understanding the schematics.
That should do it! Remember, we're looking for both the schematics for the device and the core that can power it!
My love. Must I wait forever?
Why won't you come to me, my love?
If you so much as squawk, I will fill you full of arrows.
I think that's the text we're looking for!
Byz go tell chief you want talk.
One less Goblin to deal with.
You dare steal from me? Krif voth ahkrin!
Ah. Korthor's awake.
My priests will make quick work of you! Luft Dinokii!
The shadows move, adept. Watch yourself!
Wait! I don't wish to fight. Let us talk.
Eyes to the sky! Another group!
Good luck!
Curse it, I know he left some money in here.
Found it! Time to get drinking!
That fool better have saved some for me!
Congratulations. You've passed the first trial.
To arms!
Yeah, they bested the finest sloths, drunkards, and fools we had to offer!
Adorable. Shall we give them a pendant?
I say, let's see how these soft skins fair against a real challenge!
Thank the Eight it's quiet today. Did you hear what happened to Dame Dabienne in Koeglin Village?
She said some stranger showed up and got her set loose. She was lucky. You don't find people like that every day.
I have a big nose.
It's good to know the war hasn't taken all the heroes from this world. Gives me some hope we'll get through this.
Enough of this! Now you shall die!
Stop!
An enchanted saddle-warmer? You're too generous, Sir Brice. I don't go riding often these days, but I do appreciate the gesture.
Fools! You cannot stand against the might of Molag Bal!
The Eye may be fragile. Please let me examine it.
Cease your meddling, mortal. The Master has plans for the Redguard.
You make it hard to resist your advances, but I don't want to rush into anything.
Quite the little fighter. We're not done with you yet!
Indeed I would, Yarelion â€¦ if that were truly the case. I'm afraid you gentlemen will have to excuse me now.
Hah! You're too late! I've found him. The Redguard is mine!
My master has plans for your pure soul, Merric. You should feel honored.
Welcome to the fight, comrade. Claws out, and watch yourself!
More coming. Brace yourself!
What was that voice?
So does that mean you will consider my request for your hand?
Perhaps you should tell him the truth, Ilise. That you and I plan to sell the estate and elope to Summerset Isle!
I had an awful battle with some monsters over this way.
Go on without me. I â€¦ uh â€¦ have to do something over here.
Well, here we go. Please stay close!
Now let's see if this works. It sure stinks!
I found this in Skyrim, at the bottom of a lake.
Here goes!
Is it working?
It took so long before I found Belarata. Well! Let's begin.
What's that noise?
There it is! Good luck!
"Our fates through the years are tied. A lovers' kiss? Not one denied."
"Our hearts awoke from blissful sleep, where battles break and maidens weep."
"Away to war, not long to part, with sword enchanted by his sweet heart."
"A lover's bond forever more, to keep each lover's heart in store."
Too sweet, even for me, but what can you do, yes?
Who? What happened here?
Something terrible issues from the ruins! The Bloodthorns have released an Ayleid horror.
Come, she waits.
A sword with a poem etched into it. Also, the name "Belarata."
I'm off to Deepwoods! Wish me luck!
I'm his now! Beware when next we meet!
There's too much power! I can't contain it!

The Keep has been abandoned for ages, sealed by unyielding frostâ€”the locals say that it is haunted. Despite this, I hope to reclaim my ancestral home.nnShould ill-fortune befall me, I have left these Speaking Stones behind to tell my tale.
The Keep has been abandoned for a generation, its entrances sealed by decades of accumulated layers of ice.  The locals keep away, frightened by stories of a witch's curse on the Direfrost family.

There is an undeniable presence here, and dread consumes me. Despite my fear, I cannot help but investigate. Should ill-fortune befall me and I do not survive, I have left these Speaking Stones behind to tell my tale. I will start in the Main Hall.
It looks clear now! Hurry. Meet me back at the manse!
By the Green, I could use a drink. Smell that fresh brew!
Stendarr. My head!
Giant snakes? Ahhh!
Here they come!
Isâ€¦ is this the way out?
Netches are worse than kwama! Oh, what have I done?
Hold a moment. We should speak.
Everyone! Gather around the fire. Our visitor has introduced me to a new delicacy. This one thinks it will be a most fragrant experience.
This door bears a threefold seal. All of the runes must be found and activated to open it.
Ysanne, why are you here? I don't think gawking at that knight is such a good idea.
What do you mean, not a good idea? You expect me to show pity for someone who's working with slavers?
You really believe that? She's a Knight of the Flame. There's no way she was working with the slavers.
Then why'd the constable have her locked up? You don't have an answer for that, do you?
I don't understand the constable's reasoning, but I have enough sense to realize that something's not right here.

Do you still seek to free us with Sirdor's Stone? We already told youâ€”we don't need your kindness. It comes ages too late. And if you think we won't flay you when we're freeâ€”we believe sharp laughter is the way your kind would respond.
This is â€¦ unpleasant. Our mind feels â€¦ pulled apart â€¦.
This light â€¦ reminds us of the sun.
You will die as Sirdor did, and we will drink you, as well.
I have returned, my love!
<<1>>, we've got a new ally here!
My love? I cannot â€¦ your sword! Where is â€¦.
A pure soul, Doshia. Don't fail me.
Kyne, give me strength.
Agh. Aaaaaaaagh!
I can't wait to see my family.
Noooo! Aaaaaaaaaaaaagh!
You lied? Stay away from me!
You are tired! Let me come closer!
You are not <<1>>! Get back!
Augh!
My friend, no! What are you doing?
My head! I need a moment.
B'vek, I'll have my revenge.
Your revenge, your silk was worthless. Mine was the finest quality.
Did an Ashlander tell you that?
I hate your face!
<<1>>, at long last I return!
<<1>>! You have been gone only a day, but it feels like an age.
Yes, true. But you â€¦ where have you been?
Each day is an age without you.
It is a long story, but come! Aetherius awaits!
Yes, together forever, as was always meant to be.
So long, my friend, and thank you. For everything!
Ha! Durak. You say we betrayed you, but the Spirit Wardens and the Midnight Union were never allies.
Indeed. We serve two very different mistresses. Our dream is your nightmare. Welcome to the new world, Abbot!
How's he doing?
He'll live, but he won't be swinging a sword anytime soon.
Stay with him. We may need to move fast if they attack again.
You never forget that smell. A Dragon Priest's tomb.
A frost barrier. Look for a way to bring it down.
Worthless!
Now, let's see if I can dislodge this.
Something's â€¦ happening.
Fire and brimstone!
Agrakh will be pleased with your head!
Ah, you've won this round!
This doesn't seem right â€¦.
Ahh, my favorite mortal. Shalidor finally figured out how to let you in. You're here to kick me out, I know. But fighting isn't really my thing. Haskill?
Very good, sir. Ahem. Have at you, adept. We will now face each other in honorable combat. On your guard.
Exactly. Now, say goodbye to the nice mortals, Haskill.
Just remember to point the wand away from you, dearie!
Where's my catalog? I must document my finds!
All right, that's enough. Break it up you two!
Let's move.
Look, pup, someone to play with you!
Puppy doesn't like you, does he?
It is clear, that Arenthia was where they were going.
The it is settled we attack at dawn!
That would lead to much unnecessary bloodshed. We should see if we can rouse the local population.
We do not have time for that. Who knows what tortures the Mane is enduring.
I agree, but we need a plan. We need to know what is going on with Arenthia.
Perhaps a more subtle approach is needed. Our new ally has already proven useful, and may do so again.
Hey, you wanna dance?
Yeah, you've earned it, Trelan. Let's go!
You don't want this war, <<1>>.
This should let you talk to the Drublog without bloodshed.
Fresh meat for The Crucible, eh?
Let's feed 'em to the Durzog!
Good idea. Get 'em boys!
Hmph. I guess that'll do. Open the gates!
What madness is this, restless spirits? Why have you left the sanctity of the Coiled Path?
Be calm, spirits. Trust in the wisdom of the Ghost Snake.
How are the house repairs going?
Slow. I was having new mortar shipped in, but the constable won't let them unload the cargo from the ship.
Strange days. The slavers, the ship, and now this knight in the stocks â€¦ our peaceful village isn't so peaceful any more.
Easy, just put the sword down.
Quiet! How many more of you are there?
You're Veiled Heritance, aren't you? I should ask you the same thing.
Oh this is an easy one!
Over here! Untie Khajiit!
Piss off!
Another outsider! But this one â€¦ I have seen this one in my visions. We must speak.
This is an outrage! I want to speak to the man in charge of this tribe, you crazy woman!
Everyone, stay back! No one's getting on or off that ship until further notice.
Argh!
That look on your face was amazing!
Did you get it? Did your invitation arrive?
Rub it in, why don't you? If you must know, Shad Astula has rejected me. Again.
Nonsense. I'm sure it's just a clerical error. You'll be in the Academy next season, for sure!
New challengers appear from the cold wastes. Are they worthy enough to face The Pack? Let the games begin!
Let's get in there and show those orcs whose town this is!
Go back to your homes. You'll be much safer there.
Impressive. Let's see if they can handle something a little harder, eh?
The Green Lady is mine by right. I have captured the Silvenar. She must yield to me.
Are you hurt, Elf?
<<1>>! Stay back!
Though I am in Silvenar's city, I have power. Chieftain, cut them down!
I warned you, <<1>>! You chose to stand against your people!
No! Brother! Stay your hand!
Go! See where they have gone. Hurry!
I'm sure we'll have the situation resolved soon. Until then, you'll have be to be patient.
My daughter! This is not loyalty. You're this hound's pet!
<<1>>. You have much to answer for.
I leave <<1>> to you, <<2>>.
The Hound â€¦ I know who he truly is. It does not bode well.
Stay beside me, friends. We face the cult together!
Kyne's Breath. Can it be? The Five Hundred Companions?
Sinmur is dead. You have won a great victory this day!
Rise Jorunn, Skald King. Rise and greet me as the true champion of the north.
You have united not just the Nords. The ancient Elves and the crafty lizard folk stand with us as well.
Your champions! We've met. A hard road lies ahead of you. But for now, savor this victory.
Companions! Three cheers for the Skald King and his brave champions! Wormcrushers and giantslayers!
Again!
Once more!
Gather your forces, Skald King, and champions like those here today. The hardest task awaits. The Worms are servants of a more sinister force.
Coldharbour beckons. The veil grows thin. You must convene a great moot in Mournhold, Skald King. You have an invasion to plan.
For the Pact and the north!
Ysgramor! I am not worthy.
I had help, my liege.
Thank you, Ysgramor!
What force, my liege?
Yes, my liege! For the Pact!
Companions! We ride to Sovngarde!
Yes. Let's get you inside, dear. This has been a difficult day. But I'm here now.
I â€¦ I think I need to lie down for a moment.
Get away from my things!
Not so fast there, Shalidor. Only invited guests at the Chateau. We have standards, you know.
Damn you, Mad God!
Don't let the door hit you on the way out, Shally.
Annnd â€¦ off you go!
Just the two of us. Now we can talk in peace.
I sense changes coming to our Vale, whether we wish it or no.
It looks as like there's some fight in our challengers, after all. Take them down!
Gahhh!
Very well then. Now you will face us.
I've known this clan for years. We've never been allies, but this hostility is unexpected.
This one thanks you, stranger. Please, come to meet in the storehouse!
Thanks to you, young one. I will find my own escape now.
You fight well! Thank you for freeing me, friend!
Haskill? Oh, Haskill! Show them what the Wabbajack can do!
The pigs, Haskill! Toss those huggable, squeezeable piglets!
Now you've gone and done it. I've never seen Haskill so angry! At someone else, I mean.
Be wary. Talk to these "guests" carefully before you try to throw anyone out.
I can hear you, Shally! Don't bother my guests!
You're the only one that thinks you're funny, Mad God!
Only two more to go. This trial is child's play.
I'm going to bind you to haunt a little old lady in Wayrest! Does that sound fun, Shally?
Hardly.
Those poor souls. Sheogorath's "family."
How do you keep getting back in here? I blame Haskill.
Apparently, not everything is under your control!
Not yet, anyway.
So much for Uncle Leo.
Come now, is that any way to mourn a loss? Really!
Why do you disturb me?
She's gone. You're too late.
â€¦ as our agreement stipulates, "By fire and sword."
Drublog do not slaughter those who keep us fat with plunder!
<<1>> insists Velyn Harbor must burn.
Tell your "Captain" my decision stands!
Back inside, you s'wit.
Intruders! Over here!
The constable says be ready.  He's got a plan.
Of course, of course. Care to join me? Oh, never mind. I'm going.
He won't be pleased.
Ha! Then he will meet my fist and those of my people!
Leave me, dog! I've heard enough barking.
There they are! Get 'em!
I made it! Did you miss me? Find anything exciting before I got here?
Hey, handsome! Did you send this fine bottle of wine to little old me?
What? Are you talking to me?
No, I'm talking to the other good-looking House Dres guy over there. Look, if you didn't send this to me, just say so and I'll show my gratitude to somebody else.

Well, I'm the only House Dres courier who delivers wine in Mournhold, so that bottle must have come from my supply. And it certainly looks good next to you. You mentioned gratitude. How thankful exactly are you thinking?
Why don't you come upstairs and find out? Someone has to help me drink this wine.
Good. You've arrived.
Kneel down, lover. Let's have some fun.
Well, that was fun! Hey! Didn't you see my signal? Go get the key!
Flyin', flyyin' in the sky,  cliff racer flies so high, flyinnn'
Flyin', flyyin' in the sky,  cliff racer flies so high, flyinnn'
Flyin', flyyin' in the sky,  cliff racer flies so high, flyinnn'
Don't worry. You won't see me again if I can help it.
Wait, Iâ€”
This is an outrage! Let me speak to the man in charge of this tribe, you crazy woman!
This is madness! What kind of people are you? I demand to speak to the man in charge here!
Follow me.
There are just a few of us left. I don't know how much longer we can hold.
The Colovians were at our doorstep. Ask Shazah about that. Now some of them are hiding within the fort.
<<1>> is up here. Mind your feet.

Welcome one and all to the Frozen Arena! The site for today's grand melee! The winner of this contest will face the most feared  collection of monsters in all of Tamriel! Without further ado, begin the melee!
About time you got here. What took you so long?
Come on. Let's see what's down here.
No, this can't be right. Damn it! These tunnels were supposed to be sealed off. Well, into the fire and all that. Follow me.
The Nords have been sent packing, to their Halls of the Dead!
And there go the Altmer! High Elves, laid low!
These Dunmer will never again know the wonders of Morrowind!
The Argonians should feel right at home, face down in the mud!
No time to lick their wounds. The Khajiit are defeated!
And there we have it! The winners of the Grand Melee!
What? No! How did you find those clothes? I hid them so well!
I would have chosen otherwise.
Test Say
You conniving little witch! This was my idea!
Alits? Really? Search around. There should be a door somewhere nearby. I'll keep an eye out.
Let me guess. The door won't open? There's got to be something controlling it. Look around a bit. And watch out for those creatures. They're â€¦ ugly.
You got past my men. Did Tharayya put you up to this? She's still out there, isn't she? Kill these fools.
Pathetic! I'll have to do this myself!
Hmm. Just a moment. Aelif recognizes this set up.
You must destroy the totems before the Hound comes. Quickly, now!
Yes! These crystals control access to the room ahead. Comrade, focus on that first crystal.
By the Mace! It worked! Comrade, come to this crystal here. Merric, you focus on the one by the door.
Sheogorath's "Uncle" is a Flesh Atronach. Why am I not surprised?
I've got it!
I hate to say it, but I told you so. You should've listened to me.
That's it! Merric, you hold that beam. Aelif will use the last crystal to open the door. We are almost there.
I wouldn't say it too loud if I were you. There's another set of stocks right there next to the constable.
I don't care if the constable was brainwashed by some cult. I still say there's something suspicious about that woman.
Well. You aren't at all what I was expecting.
Let's talk.
Just one more beam and we are through this door!
This is going to be so much fun!
Our army moves on Carzog's!
Q4449 00 Spawn Bestow 2
Q4449 00 Spawn Bestow 3
Success! Let's go. Sees-All-Colors must be close.
Feels like the old days, Aelif. Let's get this done!
Commander <<1>>, what's wrong?
The Bloodthorns have raised a spectral army from the depths of the ruins. We can't defeat them!
Get the wounded back to the fortress. We'll put an end to this!
Remember, you can take clothes from hampers or off dead Sea Drakes.

Shazah â€¦ I've missed you. You left me alone in the dark.
Ahh, you remember her?
Shazah? Is that you? You're alive? You're safe?
Of course I'm alive. Safe and sound â€¦.
Your sister is safe. Her soul has been purified by darkness. Come, join her. Come join your sister.
Oh, you want her free? Here is your sister, free. Your sister, my new Dark Mane!
Let her go! Show yourself, you bastard! I'll take your face off with my claws.
It seems I have the wrong sister â€¦ weakling child!
Ah, my old friend! I thought we'd lost you.
Fine! I'll take care of you myself.
What? It â€¦ it can't be!
So good to see you all again, my friends! I'm glad we all made it here safely.
Vanny! You're alive! That's wonderful!
Ah, dear Nalia! My heart fills with delight at the sight of you! Yes, I am safe.
Where have you been, old friend? Trying to win the war all by yourself again?

Well, then, you have our thanks. I'm not sure we could have gone on without â€¦ without Vanus â€¦.
Cheer up, dear Nalia. I'm here now. But our mission isn't finished. We have to destroy the planar vortex and end the Planemeld.
Do you have a plan, old friend?
I know what we need to do, I'm just not sure how we go about doing it. We need to discuss this with the Fighters Guild. We need a council of war.
Dark Mane! Attend me! May the shadows of your dead god imbue you with strength!
Praise Tall Papa that the ogrim couldn't find the keys to the cages.  I've almost got these knots untied. Help me finish so I can get out of here.
Hillid! Show yourself, you honorless swine! I trusted you!
I'd do it again in a heartbeat, you simpering goat!
Skordo sent you, didn't he? Thank Tall Papa!
I won't kill your precious Fariel. When we take Woodhearth, I'll keep her for myself.
What? Who areâ€¦
Speak of her now, snakecharmer.
Did you hear? Some puffed up Altmer took the great stone out from Mourning Springs and an army of skeletons rose from the depths!
Yes! But some walker was there to crush them back down with lightning, walls of water â€¦ real five-clawed stuff!
Yes! And a good thing, too! This one does not like to think about what would have happened otherwise.
Still nothing.
What do they think they are playing at? We paid them, yes?
Who knows? Maybe they got caught? It wouldn't be the first time.
@@frustrated growl@@ What do they think they are playing at? We paid them, yes?
Climbs, if they don't make the drop soon, let's cut our losses and make for the mainland.
This one does not like it, but perhaps you are right. Still, keep checking, will you?
All right! I've been waiting for this!
<<1>>, my friend! You have fish to share with <<2>> today?
No, they are hiding! Sometimes they sneak a nibble, but that is all. Perhaps something is wrong with the water?
Ah, perhaps so. The storm, it has broken a great many things. Why not the water, as well?
Three and six. A good haul.
Ah, our friends! They must have recovered from the storm, yes?
It had to happen sooner or later. "The crossed tree never falls," or so they say.
Still, all these soldiers mucking about â€¦ it makes me nervous.
You worry for nothing, little one. Their roots have grown for many years. It will take more than a few elves to tear them up.
You have meddled with my affairs long enough. It is time to end this.
Yes. The time has come to end this. This evil.
What are you doing here? Your ward is broken, Ansei! You are no threat to me!
I cannot believe <<1>> let those sea snakes into port again!

At least the Dominion has arrived. Maybe they can talk some sense into the Headwoman.
Or replace her. <<1>> can only benefit from Dominion rule. If that Betmer buffoon is allowed to continue in her post, I â€”

This one knows there is an entrance to the tower somewhere nearby! Kamu â€¦ must â€¦ get â€¦ in!

Oh, this just gets better and better!
Darien! Mind your tongue!

Well, when you put it that way, there are a lot of lovely ladies that need to be saved â€¦.

Yes, well, be that as it may, we launch our assault on the Chasm immediately. The King needs to talk to the champion and I must discuss some final details with the mages. The rest of you have your own preparations to see to, I'm sure.
Citizens of Arenthia, bright moons hang above us.

Hey, Aruz! I owe you one! For Borgath!
You are undone by your own heroics, dog. I may not be a lich, but I have an army of undead!

You will die. You will die and then you will join my army.
There is no one but the dead here, hero. We made sure of that.
Well done, little mortal. You killed Ifriz and I didn't have to lift a finger. Delightful!
You and I will meet again, I think. I look forward to seeing what trouble you get into next.
You and I will likely meet again

Onward! Ha ha!

Two moons smiled on us and danced us across ja-Kha'jay! And now, once we are wedâ€”

Of course, love! How could <<1>> forget? But once we are together, we bring our dance to the world, yes? On one of your father's finest ships!
It will be wonderful, my dear! But come, you must speak with mother! Surely, we cannot marry without her consent?
Of â€¦ of course, my love. Next time we see her, she will know all we plan and we will ask her for her blessing. Aheh. How could she say no?
Our ship has sunk. We must find someone to hire us until the next comes in.
Perhaps we should ask the local government? They will need help rebuilding after that gale, no?
I'm not too keen on that. A little town like this won't be able to pay up front. We're leaving on the next boat we can get, right?

Here. We'll drink it together and I'll fight by your side till the end.
Until the end.
If you don't mind me saying, you're quite easy on the eyes Thiirril. You should consider the possibilty of dating a fine specimen like myself.

You may begin.

Zeht's Tears! We are beset by these tragedies most cruelly.

There! That woman, follow her!
I think I can actually sense the blight attempting to corrupt my mind. I've never felt anything like this.
You see! A vision of a Wood Elf. That must be where we should go. Come on, Hallowed.

Why should it be that it would upset her more now than at any other time?
She has just brought on so much new help of late, it is likely costing her dearly each day that we have no water to sell.
Greenhill has been lost to us.
Stay where you are and remain our eyes and ears.
Our mortal hands will reach out to you soon.
Remain faithful dark sister.
Hail, friend. I am glad you have come. I have forgivness to ask of you.
What is this?
My brother and I threw the stones that broke your windows. I've some coin and a few goats you may take as recompense.

We turned on each other so quickly. May those responsible eat sand for driving us to this.
Master Pircalmo, Lady Alanya. Please accept my apology.
Um, don't worry! I thought it was my fault too!
â€¦ What he means to say is, these sorts of misunderstandings happen. We're not the type to hold a grudge.
Right. Yes. That. That's what I meant.
I'd like to extend you a more permanent offer here. We could use someone with your diligence and knowledge.
I don't really follow. I don't want to put Alanya atâ€”
Dear, she's offering you a job. You'd be the town mage.
Really? I mean, yes! Absolutely. Uh, if it's all right with you, dear.
I think I'd quite like that. No more stone tables, though, Ranneth.
It would be our honor to have you both here.
Prepare the cave temple! It's a suitable place for a celebration.
Hello, Angiente. If you don't mind, I'd like to be alone.
I never see you doing any work, Angiente. You should try it. Now go away.
Even the water here seems to be somehow tainted.
The corruption has spread to these plants as well. It's like they're dead â€¦ but not dead at the same time.
Burn!
You will die first.
You life ends now!
Why won't you die?
Into the ground. Hurry!
Quickly. Bury yourself!
Your bones will turn to ash!
Look. Another one.
General Malgoth, the troops â€¦ half of them are dead! The other half â€¦.
Are dying, including us. This is poison. The villagers poisoned themselves to poison us.
What do you mean?
The Meat Mandate you idiot! Elphirion knew she couldn't win on the field, but she'll still manage victory. To the Nereid temple. Perhaps we can beg a cure.
Will there be no end to these interruptions?
I expect we're nearing the conclusion of this sad story.
Get my daughter out of here, Sergeant! I'll hold them off.
Listen, everyone! We're going to the Hollow City. Anyone who doesn't want to leave can stay here with Bernt. But real Nords will come with me!

It invoked the Right of Theft, and commanded we march against the Dominion.
Place the essences in the magicka conduits. That should disrupt the binding spell that seals the cage.

Turn backâ€¦.
Back to your master, wretched thing!
By Stendarr! Are you all right Aelif?
<<1>>! Thank the Hist!

We were finishing up when they appeared. They were after the crystal and tome. How did they know? How did they know about this place?
Aelif does not know. Merric, this whole thing is madness. She has us hunting Daedra, and now they come calling on our doorstep â€¦.
Aelif! Behind you!
Come face me, if it's the bow you desire.
The bow is a boon to our army; you will not have it.
You will soon join us and fight at Malgoth's side.
I hope you've prepared for undeath.
Naemon warned me about you, and I prepared.
You will die, and then you will serve us!
You'll get used to this realm. As will all of Valenwood.
Aelif, Merric. I do not rest easily.
Dark moons! Guildmaster Iceblade, what's happening?
I was murdered, comrades. Seek my killer. Let me find peace.

Interesting. Very interesting. Aelif has her suspicions.
Our forces are gathered and the time has come to strike fast and strike hard. Time is not on our side, so we must make every moment count.
Now. To battle!
It worked! I did it! I can't believe it!
Good luck.
You've â€¦ freed us.
Rid-Thar-ri'Datta â€¦ the First Mane?
You have arrived in Reaper's March at a critical time. The soul of the Khajiiti people, and the entire Dominion, are in crisis.
What were you doing down there? You saw, didn't you?
The Wood Elf known as Finedrin has been found guilty of the following crimes â€¦.

Stealing rotten tomatoes and other refuse from stablemaster Semiral's midden-heapâ€¦.
Dumping said refuse on the head of the Altmer commander, Faruin during his visit to the clanmother â€¦.

For all of these crimes, this one sentences him to the stocks until such time as he shows proper repentance.
This person is our enemy! Quickly! Kill the intruder!

Troops are already inside, fighting and holding ground, causing a distraction so that you can deal with Molag Bal's ability to call reinforcements.
Enough with the games, Sheogorath. Are you going to relinquish the island to us or not?

Skordo the Knife, pride of the Fighters Guild, will aid you in your initial assault. Let his strength sweep away your foes and keep you safe.
The lamia will join you for your initial assault. Allow her ferocity and determination to lead you to victory.
Darien the Brave joins you on your first assault. Allow his courage to be your beacon in the darkness.
Close the reinforcement portal. That is your first priority. Gabrielle and her forces will join you then for the push to the Labyrinth.
Zur the Khajiit will give you his wisdom when you reach the inner sanctum of the palace. Let his knowledge aid you in your path.
Malkur, the reader of the ruins, will help you upon reaching the labyrinth. Allow his knowledge of the daedric culture to guide your path.

The dark power of Angof is yours to command. Use his seeds to call forth followers to aid you in the fight. Even in times like these, dark magics may be necessary.

With the power of the Lights of Meridia gathered, call forth their strength in time of need to use its power to abolish your foes.
That is your ultimate objective. If we are to end the Planemeld, we must disrupt the planar vortex and cease its destructive storm.
As you approach the final gate, embrace the shadows and your companion Faralina of the Shadow Walkers. Let her guide you through shadows to defeat any beast who stands in your way.
As you approach the portal, lay aside your thoughts of the past. Embrace the help of the lamia as your final push to the portal wages on.
In the end, as you make your final assault towards the portal, leverage the power of One-Eye who now holds the power of the crown.

Take your brave companion and venture forth! Close the reinforcement portal so that our forces can wage war on the Daedric Prince. Then open the Labyrinth and lead us to the planar vortex. Our destiny is in your hands!
Uncle Sheo? Are we going somewhere?
Yes, little one. You're coming with me. Home to the Shivering Isles! Won't that be nice?

I can do this. Nothing to it.

I'm back. I didn't jump in. It was too windy.
Y'ffre's bones! What in Oblivion is he doing? We have to stop him! Hurry!
I'll begin the rebinding spell. You take care of that mage!
Now, use the blood rune on the final seal! Quickly!
That portal up there is our final destination? Doesn't seem too far. There is an entire army of Daedra between here and there, but it's not too far at all.
You! Tharn wants to speak to you! Go to the Daggerfall Mages Guild! Quick quick!
You! Tharn wants to speak to you! Go to the Vulkhel Guard Mages Guild! Quick quick!
You! Tharn wants to speak to you! Go to the Davon's Watch Mages Guild! Quick quick!
I know, dear.
Whew, it's cold out here.
We need a launcher pointed in that direction! Brace for impact!
Klovag â€” about my wall ideaâ€¦.

I cannot follow you into Tu'whacca's Sanctum. My mission leads elsewhere.
Please Andur. Stop burning everything. The fire â€¦ it hurts.
I will burn this entire forest down if I have to!
You will go no further.
For Lord Dagon!
What? You son of a bitch!
Gah! Are you insane? Get away from me, you brutish she-troll!
