You deal with the crystal! We'll take care of our new guests.
Is someone out there? I could use a little help in here!
What's this? Who disturbs Captain Blackheart at his rest?nnCome a long way to die.
Let me fix that complexion for you!
Ah, that was delicious! Why don't we head over to the pools and take a nice, relaxing soak?
Ah, my dear <<1>>. You've grown lovelier in my absence.
No! You cannot do this! I cannot fail!
Let my power flow through you - let it consume you. Let it battle back the darkness. Feel its power ebb and flow through your veins. Fight the darkness! Destroy this all! Destroy it!
Farewell â€¦ my friend.
This one can't believe you conquered such a beast.nnBakkhara will handle the ritual altar. Finally, the Canonreeve's folly can be undone.
There's too much power! I can't contain it!
Keep the power contained, just as we practiced!
Something's wrong! His body isn't like the others!
So you're the one who's taken our blessed stone! I should have killed you when I had the chance, you damned peasant!
When you're ready to leave this place, let me know.
Pellingare!
He's dead, you bastard! Yahyif is dead!
Give me one reason why I shouldn't kill you!
Two kings and a queen with barely a thimble of patience between them. Reaching a compromise will be no small task, I promise you.
Sir!
Careful with that, you clumsy fool! Do hurry it up. We're missing everything!
I never weary of your charms, Lady Laurent.
Vanus Galerion, as I live and breathe! Thank you so much for this opportunity. I had no idea the summit was to be held on the legendary island of Stirk!
It seemed a fitting choice. It was here that the leaders of the First Era assembled the All Flags Navy to do battle with the Sload.
I can't wait to see what surprises Molag Bal's realm has in store for us!
We are waging war, not embarking on a sightseeing expedition, milady.
Fear not, Vanus. I can take care of myself and my useless lump of a manservant.
Stibbons! Haven't you finished tying those bags yet? You really are hopeless.
Farewell, milady. We must dash. We're expected at the summit.
Here's Telenger the Artificer, himself! Must it always take a crisis to pull you away from your toys, Telly?
Vanus. Your robes smell of failed experiments and your words of failed wit.
Tell me, Telly, what Dwemer rubbish pit did you crawl out of this week?
You really must learn to respect your betters, old friend.
Do let me know when one happens by, won't you?
I don't have the time or the energy, Telenger, so I'll bid you good day.
Captain Alphaury. Has the island been secured?
Aye. All ships in the area have been diverted away from the island, and the wards are in place.
And the alliance leaders?
They'll be here any moment. You three should get over there as soon as you can.
We're on our way. Thank you, Captain.
We must make haste.
I can't imagine venturing outside the city. There are so many horrible places out there.
I heard the Lightless Oubliette is the worse, Molag Bal only keeps his greatest enemies there.
As long as we stay inside the walls, Molag Bal's minions shouldn't be able to drag us off to the Court of Contempt.
I heard that Molag Bal is trying to pull Tamriel into Coldharbour.
You just heard that? Didn't you know that's why we're here?
He must be using lots of Daedra and some sort of machine to accomplish that!
Enter my mind, Vestige, and walk with me through the shadows of past events.
Fadalia, your life is spared. Leave, and never return.
So the Wood Elves have a friend who's not afraid to fight? Good. Give me your best.
My disciples, this stranger speaks the truth. We must go to the graveyard.
I will explain more soon. But for now, call upon an arbiter. She must hear my confession as well.
Leki grant me strength â€¦ I must not delay any longer!
Ahh, quite the view from up here, eh? I meant the landscape. Don't get any ideas.
All right, let's find the rest of me! Try searching the Wormie camps, or knocking some skeletons around until my bits fall out.
Efficient little nitwits. Could be a part of me in every skeleton here!
Soldier, I appreciate your vigilance, but the Argonians in <<c:1>> are guests. Refrain from any further displays of zeal or I'll have you scrub down the barricade. Dismissed.
Follow me, Vestige, and learn of the events that precipitated our current crisis.
That was my femur! Wait, no, my femur bends to the left. Carry on!
Ha, that tickles!
Look at all the dirt on my bones! I used to bathe weekly to keep myself presentable.
My pelvis is filthy! What did the Wormies do, use it as a shovel?
Ah, that's the last one. Quickly, now! Drop my pieces on the ground and I'll put myself back together.
Sai Sahan is where? Oh no â€¦
<<1>>? What have you done?
What will you make us lose this time, <<1>>?
You should have left, <<1>>.
<<1>> will not forgive you again.
Why, <<1>>? Why return?
My part in the story began when I awoke on the steps of the Abbey of the Moth Priests, with no memory of my prior life.
The Moth Priests took pity upon me and brought me into their fold. I was weak and near death.
The master commands your death.
<<1>>! You were banished, yet you dare return?
Die, bloodsuckers!
<<1>>, listen to me! We're in danger. Necromancers are trying to kill the Barrowbough!
You warn of danger. <<1>>, who leveled nations with his girth!
It was there I first set eyes upon the Elder Scrolls and devoted my life to their study.
Merciful Stendarr, hear my prayer. I've never prayed to the Divines before. Even when my wifeâ€¦ even when you took my wife, I accepted it as fate. But At'avar, how can I accept that?
The Scrolls allowed me to glimpse the very fabric of reality, but each profound insight dimmed my vision and eventually left me permanently blinded to the light of the world.
That â€¦ that was a mistake. But if the Worm cult gets its way, we will walk the world once more! Our bones will destroy the cities of Nirn and there will be nothing we can do to stop them!
If anyone deserves your mercy, it is At'avar. Please, Stendarr, free him from this curse. Bring me back my son.
Together? Since when have you done anything that wasn't for yourself?
My friend, make him see reason!
The first companion, Lyris Titanborn, daughter of giants, was the mightiest warrior in the service of the Emperor.
Next, Abnur Tharn, a powerful sorcerer and Grand Chancellor of the Imperial Elder Council.
The Redguard swordmaster Sai Sahan, leader of the Imperial Dragonguard.
The Imperial Emperor, Varen Aquilarios, who attempted to light the Dragonfires and failed.
And finally, Mannimarco the traitor. The King of Worms. A powerful necromancer, and your executioner.
The time has come, Champion.
Stendarr protect us all.
There it is. The Dragonfire brazier. Mannimarco, you're certain this will work?
It will work, my liege. The Amulet of Kings will rekindle the Dragonfires, and ensure your rightful place as Emperor. You have my word.
It better work, Mannimarco, or you'll find your neck at the business end of my axe.
My Lord, I wonder if you'd muzzle your half-giant pet? She really is annoying.
Enough, both of you! We are here to ensure My Lord's rightful claim to the Ruby Throne.
Quickly, now! Into the portal!
Abnur, begin the ritual. I have a destiny to fulfill.
Hello, what's this?
Tongues of Xarxes! What is that thing?
Make it go away! Make it go away!
The companions assemble once more. Travel to the harborage; it is time for our final preparations.
By the lighting of the Dragonfires, I claim my rightful lineage! By the fires of creation, let me be reborn! By the will of Akatosh, I proclaim myself â€¦ Dragonborn!
Stay back! This blade must not be touched!
Varen Aquilarios, you are no heir to Alessia! You will pay for your sacrilege! The veil between Tamriel and Oblivion tears and splits asunder!
Unlock the tower door!
This isn't supposed to happen! What's the meaning of this? Mannimarco, what have you done?
What's happening? The sky is opening up! This is bad! This is very bad!
Thank you, living one. I will relish this vengeance and then enjoy my rest.
Behold the fate of the King of Worms.
Stop. Before you enter this village, a word with you.
Please! No more! It was a misunderstanding, great one! Let me serve you. Let me prove my loyalty. No more, I beg of you!
Mannimarco's torment will be endless. The God of Schemes will use him to set an example. All who follow him will know, you cannot hope to betray the greatest of betrayers.
I cannot help but pity him, despite all he has done.
But, this is not why you were called here, Vestige. Come. Sai Sahan would speak with you first.
We should not tarry from our task.
Gullible fools! The veil between Oblivion and this world has been torn! My master, Molag Bal, is free to claim Tamriel for his own!
Oops! Are my vines getting in your way?
I'll open a portal to hasten your journey.
Akatosh! Forgive me! Have mercy on our souls!
You've done your part. Get back to <<1>> when you can.
Psst. Over here!
There you are.
Wow. I wish <<1>> could have seen that thing.

Long ago it was writtenâ€”so long as the Amulet of Kings was borne by Alessia's heirs, Tamriel would be protected from the forces of Oblivion. But the Soulburst tore the veil between worlds, and gave Molag Bal the opportunity he desired.
Thank you for freeing us! You can't imagine the things we've seen.
Those fools! What are they doing?
The town is just down the path.
Everything must follow the appropriate process, or a judgment can't be reached. We must begin again.
You have been accused of disseminating illicit materials that are an affront to Imperial law. Arrest him!
I've done no wrong. I merely studied the ancient texts. Is that a crime worthy of an Imperial prison?
That man can be rather â€¦ trying.
Don't worry, old man. You're not going to an Imperial prison. We have a very special place in mind for you.
What is this? The abbey burns!
I've read about such things, but the books don't do it justice.
I can't stand that man.
Molag Bal's Dark Anchors pierce the torn veil, and seek to draw Nirn into the depths of Coldharbour. These terrible engines of destruction have been appearing all throughout Tamriel.
The worms and their master will pay for this!
Kasura!
There!
Kasura! Are you injured? What happened?
Ah, Sai Sahan and company, at last! My pet has been waiting for you.
Thank you, friend! Meet us in Longhaven when we're all out of here. I'm sure Nivrilin will reward you for this!
Kill a few more of those overgrown lizards for me! I'll see you in Longhaven.
You have this one's gratitude. Jone and Jode protect you.
Areldur! You live!
I â€¦ perhaps you are right. Forgive an old warrior's foolish notions. This is not the time for silly dreams. You should go speak with Lyris now.
I do, though I've seen better days. The High Kinlord's power has grown.nnHe would not have been able to escape our predecessors as he has escaped us today. We need to go after him.
My lord, with your permission.
You needn't call me that anymore, Sai Sahan. We are equals now.

All those years ago, when we fought beneath our lord's banner to free the Empire from the Longhouse Emperors, we did so with a dream of freedom and peace in mindâ€”not just for the Empire, but for all of Tamriel.
Together we forged a fellowship stronger than any blade, only to see it shattered upon the rocks of deceit by one of our own.
That fellowship is no more, yet we four have assembled here, united by a single purpose. It is not vengeance that drives us, but truth and loyalty and justice.
I, Sai Sahan, steward of the Abbey of Blades, call for the Five Companions to be reforged this day.
Stay down, Keeper, you're injured.nnIf the others yet live, we should find themâ€”then deal with Rilis, if we can. He has already escaped. I will not suffer further dishonor by losing lives to him.

By the light of Stendarr, and the heart of Lorkhan, may our blade of fellowship be forged anew. And may the Vestige, our mutual friend and ally, become its tip, that we may thrust it straight into the heart of a Daedric Prince.

You're ever the optimist. An Altmer should not fear the end, Cirion.nnI would give the lives of all four of us to stop Rilis. The High Kinlord will rend Tamriel apart if he gets to the surface. And it will be our fault.
Sai Sahan is right. You are the member that we should have had all those years ago.
It is as the Scrolls foretold. The soulless one will become the brightest of five stars, and they shall guide us to the coming dawn.
Oh, please. You melodramatic sots! Fine, fine. If seeing one of your foolish prophecies come true will help to ensure the safety of the Empire, I'll play along.
There is a difference between fearing death and throwing your life away, Areldur. nnAnd as long as I lead the Keepers, you will do neither. If the others live, we'll find them.
We stand united once moreâ€”the Five Companions are reforged, and together we will strike down the God of Schemes!
Come here, my friend. I've got a few things I want to say before you go.
Jahi sent you, didn't she?
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have cut the plant. Please, spare me.
Honored leaders! You have seen the face of our enemy!
Molag Bal threatens every living being in Tamriel! The Mages Guild and the Fighters Guild have agreed to join forces to launch an assault on Coldharbour!
Your restlessness trapped us here in the first place!
There are a vast number of Elf bones in <<Ac:1>>. If we all use them together, we can drive out the invader!
Once more you bring danger upon us, then beg for our help to end it. No longer! You'll remain beneath the Barrowbough until the world forgets you!
I don't â€¦
How many more of your friends must die, Sai Sahan? Where is the Amulet of Kings?
Trust in us! Sanction our actions! Give us your blessings! We will not let you down!
Oh, that one is definitely mine. I can feel it.
We will pour every iota of our strength into those items. Take them to the crypts beneath the ruined chapel.
I am the Snake. I hide in the tall grass and close on my prey with lightning speed. I'm cunning, agile, and fierce.
Vanus is right. The Guilds are our best and only choice. Send them to Coldharbour!
It is strange to return to these mountains. Memories of youth flood my mind, each one bringing its own sorrow, or its own smile.
Kasura often said that rudeness is a weak man's imitation of strength. She is wise beyond her years. You will like her, Snow Lily.
I hate to admit it, but I agree with Emeric.
Watch. My prey does not see me coming until it's too late.
As do I. It appears that much of the distrust between our alliances was sown and nurtured by the God of Schemes.
I'm the Spinner. The village expects more of me, and I failed them.
I didn't have a choice! It was just one plantâ€”I would have died otherwise.
Molag Bal thrives on deception and chaos, but if you'll forgive me, this Alliance War is of your own making.
Let's not forget the struggles that got us to this point. We're almost home. We just have a bit further to fight.

Are you all insane? You do realize what we need to do, right? We have to fight a Daedric Prince. Amulet or no, this is going to mean more death. Vestige! Come here. I'll tell you what they're afraid to mention.
Arkay, forgive me. When I realized what they were doing to us, I tried to throw myself from this tower.
From such desperation, I found the anger and strength to resist this torment. We must slay the flesh abomination. We can do this. Together.
Countess Hakruba. Gather the surviving members of both Guilds in the <<1>>. The champion and I will go there now to open the portal.
Stibbons! Thank the Radiant Mother you're all right. When I saw <<1>> with your jewels, I feared the worst!
Poor Quintus.  Always a little clumsy â€¦ in his research, in murdering people. In â€¦ relationships.
It's Voranil! Areldur, see to him.
By the Empyrean Light! Let's hope he lives.
Ah, here come some new friends. Let's see if I've still got the touch.
Slaughter. Still delightful after all these years.
Deceive and strike. The way of the Snake is dark and calculated. Remember this.
All right? How can you say that? They have my dear Lady Laurent's jewels! She will be quite distraught if I don't retrieve them.
At least you're alive. That's something! I know a secret tunnel by the pools. I can lead you there while our friend fetches your lady's jewelry. What do you think?
Of course it is. The fact of the matter stands, however. One of the Five will need to give their life to fuel this attack, when the time comes.
So you said before the Vestige arrived. And I've already thought it over. I'll do it.
Snow Lily, no! You should not need to give your life this way. This is my dutyâ€”penance for my numerous failures. This is my chance to make things right.
The Scrolls said nothing of this moment, and so I am not bound to their dictates. Vestige, I ask that you let me do this one thing. All that has happened was because of my hubris. I shall be the one.
We'll be right behind you, Vanus.
Sire, you've done enough. This was Mannimarco's doing, not yours.
As the one who will fight the Daedric Prince, the Vestige should decide.
I don't see you leaping to volunteer, Tharn. Saving your own backside again?
Hard as it may be, Lyris, don't be an idiot. I am the only one who knows the ritual and we don't have time to teach anyone else.
That's enough. It won't be decided here and now. Vestige, come here. I have some final words for you.
Follow me. The hidden entrance will not be obvious.
Has he been slain?
He's not the model of well-being, but he lives.nnAre you satisfied, Cirion? I'm eager to pursue the High Kinlord.
Patience, Areldur. I need you to heal him. And Imiril is still unaccounted for. We'll need her to face Rilis.
The energy source is alignedâ€”I think it's animating! Kill for your masters, Stormfist!
A valiant effort, but the invasion will proceed as planned. My storm will behead Malabal Tor, and the Maormer army will feast on its remains.
The storms are powerful, now! You'll die before I let you touch the Conduit Stone!
It's too late to stop the storm, now. Your death will be the first of many.
Here, let me take care of them for you.
I am the Tiger. I use brute force to destroy my prey. I am strong, proud, and fearless.
I stand toe-to-toe with my prey and deliver a ferocious killing blow!
Use superior strength to overcome your prey. The way of the Tiger is to dominate. Remember this.
Look. Such power I have now. Almost like the old days.
You should have listened to me â€¦.
Now your nightmare begins!
Your blood tastes of the Father â€¦.
It's time for a new era to begin in Tamriel. An age of calamity and suffering.
We'll use your blood to paint the walls!
That was an excellent example of a daring display gone wrong. I will cherish your skull on my mantle. Now to burn Tamriel above!
Your bones will finish this altar. An altar for my Oraneth.
Your bodies will feed the darkness. And the darkness will win this war for the Altmer.
I run Darkshade now!
I offer these lives in honor of the Forest Mother.
This is what happens to those who defile the forest. Your bodies will feed the dirt.
You are neither the first or the last to fall. Our shadow will blanket this land.
Your death was always part of the Spinner's plan.
You've defiled the Obsidian Husk. Mephala will not be pleased.
Your bodyguards are dead, Tharayya! Where are you?
I am the Wolf. I howl and the rest of the pack responds. Sharp-toothed and hungry, we hunt together.
Working together, we take down the toughest foe.
Hunt as a pack. The way of the Wolf is to move in numbers. Remember this.
These Daedra tried to keep me from my dear Lady Laurent. It's time to make them pay!
I held back fiends and vampires here, to buy time for our people to escape. Fear and anger made me strong. We will finish this. We must!
I will send every last drop of anger, hope, and desire I possess through that staff. That will draw out the abomination. I will not fail you. I will not fail Crestshade.
Divines protect us! It's the monster!
Over there, Voranil! We've found her.
I see her. Let's hope she lives. We'll need her before the day is done.
No more! Mura will not stand for it! You won't hurt any more of Mura's friends!
Hold! This has gone on long enough!
She's going to be fine, with a little restoration magic. We should be considering how to handle the High Kinlord.
Even if we defeat him, how do we contain him? He's already escaped once.nnIf we could control Daedric magic perhaps this wouldn't have happened. What do you think, Cirion? Fight fire with fire?

Stay your tongue, Voranil. You insult your lineage by even thinking it. Does the High Kinlord's fate appeal to you so?nnWe go with my plan and divide his essence among us. He can't escape his prison if he's not whole.
On your feet, Keeper.
Imiril? My fellow Keepers? You are free? Did I succeed?
Thanks to you, the Keepers' Oath is fulfilled.
We are free from Daedric corruption. We should have heeded your warnings.
I remember â€¦.nnWhere is Rilis?
Banished from this realm. With hope, all the way to Oblivion.
Your sacrifice ensures he will never return.
You think you've beaten me? How amusing!nnHaven't you noticed that the pact I've made protects me from death?
What happens now?
We can lay our burdens down.  Say your goodbyes to those who aided us. You'll be leaving them, soon.
Thank you, my friends. For everything.
Ignore his words, Keepers. Begin the separation.
I'm not confident this will work, Cirion!
Ha ha ha! What are you lot doing? Oh, I do so love to see magic. Is that what this is? This isn't as grand as the spells I learn from the Daedra, but I don't expect much from mortal Altmer.
Remember, childrenâ€”you'll never keep me here of your own accord. Not when the Daedra fight for me.nnPerhaps you'd fare better if you had Daedra on your side! Ha ha ha!
His madness nears delirium. Ignore him, Keepers. Bind the High Kinlord!
By the Light Empyrean, the Keepers of the Banished Cells hereby condemn Rilis XII to imprisonment unending.
Oh, my. It looks like you've won. Old Rilis' days of freedom are over, it seems.
Together, my friends â€¦ focus your energy â€¦.
It's working! I can feel that â€¦ thing. It's coming! Get ready!
It's a shame you lack the power to stop me more permanently. Perhaps the Daedra could help you with that. I hear Daedric Pacts can be lucrative!
Praise the Eight and all their glory! You did it!
Meet me at the other end of the graveyard, near the southern wall. I shall look for you there.
I think we are done here and I'm eager to see what waits beyond this mortal life. Farewell. Your kindness will be remembered.
I can leave this world knowing I did my best. May Tu'Whacca guard you for your kindness to us.
My poor town. I grieve knowing so many died. Yet I am grateful that we were able prevent Tainted-Heart's creation from causing greater destruction in Rivenspire.
You should not have lit the flame! The mistress will delight in a new slave.
This doorway's been sealed. There must be another way to the summit.
We did well, stranger. I am thankful that the threat posed by that creature ended here.
I knew this day would come.
Of what do you speak, O priest?
The sea vomits forth its dead. The gods are punishing us for our refusal of shelter to the Kothringi.
You mean the plague-infected folk whose Crimson Ship we turned away?
Yes. We left them in the grip of the Knahaten Flu. And why? Because we feared.
But to give them shelter would have put our whole city at risk.
The gods tested our courage, and we failed. Mark my words, this plague of undead is our atonement.
You did it! I'm free, and not a moment to lose! Quickly, to the defense of the Orchard!
I'm free! To leave, anyway. Never liked that <<1>> much. Dour fellow.
No! Not â€”
We saved some of the townsfolk and the abomination was destroyed.
I am at peace with what we were able to accomplish here. Thank you.
Easy to say â€¦ far harder to do.
They think they have an advantage, do they? Ha! Just wait until their plan crumbles around them!
I grieve for those we lost, but I'm happy we were able to foil Reezal-Jul's plan.
Where is the Amulet of Kings?
Pick up those feet, maggots! Move! Move! Move!
Seems my secret is a secret no more.
Father? Are you all right?
Wasn't expecting to run into a beetle. It must have followed my scent.
You poisoned the johads? But why?
Father! Your wound â€¦.
My last wish was for the johads to remain within the family, but â€¦ it caused nothing but strife.
No, you can't die! Not now!
Listen! I wish for your happiness. Promise me â€¦ the johads â€¦.
We will find happiness, Father! I swear to you.
It's frosty as the edge of Skyrim up here!
Speak to me, friend. Don't be afraid.
No Direnni shall get past these gates! Do you understand me?
Quickly! We must find Kasura!
According to my notes, I need a relic called the Torch of Heirs to light the Flame, located in the Hall of the Dead.nnMy map shows the Hall down this side passage, it seems.

Did you hear that? That Khajiit doomed her own villageâ€”she's the reason it is here! Must have made a pact with the Daedra! How awkward. In future dealings with the Khajiit, try not to think about her. Think of helpful Mezha-dro! Or someone better.
I know this! The day the Elden Accord was signed! The Mane was a good leader, Hallowed. A warrior.
Make sure these orders circulate among the troops. They need to be prepared for what's to come.

That Orc must have made a deal with that Dremora Lord. He betrayed his village, doomed it to reside in Coldharbour! Stupid Orcs and their stupid fights over ugly rock huts. Not that this one has anything against Orcs. Just stupid Orcs.
Follow me, quickly! Before any more of them return!

So that elf is a traitor! He's turned on his own people for profit! Must have something to do with the Dunmer village getting pulled into Oblivion. This one is glad to see even elves can make poor life decisions.
High King Emeric of the Daggerfall Covenant.
Queen Ayrenn of the Aldmeri Dominion.
Jorunn Skald-King of the Ebonheart Pact.
Here, friend. Brackenleaf has sent me to give you the next part of your trial.
Who disturbs the Heart of the Barrowbough?
<<1>>, enough with the theatrics. You need to let us in!
<<1>>? What are you doing here? Who is with you?
The day Rid-Thar-ri'Datta became the first Mane. He had to crack some skulls, mark my words. But my people are better for it today.
Damned priests. Treating us like that. Even Shazah couldn't stomach it. But look at us. You and me, today. Shazah â€¦ I wish you were here.
Look up there! The top of the central pillar.

And now for the summit. There are many reasons not to go.nnI can hear blasting winds at the top of that ladder, and there is a chill that strikes the bone. Any manner of beast could be waiting for me. But I will not shame my family by walking away.
Can anyone hear me? What's happening?nnMy blood boils, yet I feel no pain! Somebody, help me!
Can I help you with something?
No! Stay away!
Vestige! Meet me at the Harborage. We are ready to rescue Sai Sahan.
The bone scepter? No! Please, don't wake him!
Go with Abnur! Save Sai Sahan from the Halls of Torment!
Go with Lyris! Save Sai Sahan from the Halls of Torment!
Oh, joy. We've been here less than five minutes and Sahan is already getting maudlin and weepy.
Shut up, Tharn! Don't let him get to you, Sai. Let him roll his eyes. Maybe he'll find a brain back there.
So much destruction! What could have done this?
I'm afraid I've seen this before. Keep an eye skyward, Titanborn!
I demand you release the prisoner immediately! Your detention of a Maormer citizen is in direct violation of the treaty we long ago signed with <<1>>!
Do you mean the spy we caught skulking around our wrecked ships? He stays put.
Where's my son? Help me! Please! I need to find my son!
Then I'll raise this matter with Headwoman <<1>> in <<2>>. She should know the Dominion for what they really areâ€”High Elf arrogance, at the point of a sword.
I'm so frightened. I don't know what to do.

Your life is a lie, Sai Sahan. You failed to become a sword-singer. You failed in your sworn duty to protect your Emperor. To this day your former companions mock you for your incompetence and call you a fool!
Becoming a sword-singer is child's play, Sai. I mastered it in an afternoon. Here, let me show you.
No! You are not real! I have heard your lies and borne your torment, day after day, year after year! You will not break me!
So much yelling. So much screaming. I need to stay strong. Stay strong.
Be on your guard.
Mannimarco? Here? Stay close.
Guard! Why won't you help? We need help!
Esteemed High King Emeric, I thank you for agreeing to this meeting. I would not presume to waste your time without good reason.
Cat's Eye "Key." Would you listen to these bumpkins? Who says "Key?"
We've known each other for some time, Master Galerion. You aren't known for your capricious whims. Tell me thoughâ€”who is your companion?
Your Majesty, this is Queen Ayrenn's personal representative, here to speak with you about the impending Coldharbour crisis.
Exactly. Call it Cat's Eye "Kway," like the Divines intended.
What are you on about? It's Cat's Eye "Kay." What imbecile says "Kway?"
My mother. The harbormaster.
Bumpkin.
Your Majesty, this is Skald-King Jorunn's personal representative, here to speak with you about the impending Coldharbour crisis.
So Queen Ayrenn sends her personal champion into the stronghold of her greatest enemy? Either she has a lot of faith in you, or she's trying to get you killed. Hm. I'm intrigued. Come, let us speak.
The Skald-King sends his personal champion into his enemy's stronghold? Either he has a lot of faith in you, or he's trying to get you killed. Hmm. I'm intrigued. Come, let us speak.
I have a good feeling about these tunnels. Perhaps we'll actually find Pellingare tonight.
Eyes skyward! Here it comes!
That was your opinion last night, too.
Yes. And one day some Divine will reward me for my unwavering optimism.
Come, you wretched souls. Feed me!
Oblivion take you!
And when you get there, tell all your friends who sent you back!
Tell Cariel that I hope to drop in for a visit very soon. From an upper story. She'll know what I mean.
The day is ours, my friends, but Kasura and her people have a long task ahead of them if they are to rebuild the abbey.
They're already inside. If we're lucky, they haven't made it to the heart of the Barrowbough.
So you've been mingling with the enemy, have you, Dariah? Just so you knowâ€”I already knew that.
Oh, I love to mingle, Your Majesty. I'm going to mingle their heads right off their necks one of these days.
Why would a crypt need a secret entrance?
It's a wonder there's an unplundered crypt in all of Skyrim! You Nords could learn a thing or two from the builders of Hammerfell.
Perhaps Hammerfell could also teach Nibenay the virtue of good manners.
And why are there intruders in the roots of the Barrowbough? <<1>>, what have you done?
What do you mean, "no chance of hurricanes?"
It says they're unseasonable to <<1>> this time of year.
Then what would you call the hurricane that smashed <<1>>?
Unseasonable, I suppose.
The flame of my heart now resides within you.
Carry it with honor, and protect my forest with pride. I will now return you to <<1>>.
Hunt well, and tend my forest with care.
This is the worst vacation.
What  do you mean?
Not a day here before the hurricane hits. Then a Dominion fleet smashes ashore, which means our leave is well and truly canceled.
Could've been worse. You could've introduced me to your mother.
When you put it like that â€¦.
We're gone three hours and the Maormer attack the city? Typical! Always missing the real fight.
You have to admit, the temple was interesting.
Stone, water, and talkative ghosts. What about that is interesting?
Every part?
You're hopeless.
Where is the Amulet of Kings? Tell me, or I'll gut you like a fish with your own sword!
Newest of the Briars, you have my blessing. Good luck, and return to my forest any time.
Now, let's see about this curse.
Done! Good as new.
My sweet Musi! You did it! Good girl!
Such a stubborn Elf! Perhaps your companion will be more willing to listen to reason.
They've broken through!
What a waste of time!
Obstinate fools, both of you!
The hour has arrived, Vestige. The final confrontation with the God of Schemes is at hand. The Five Companions gather at the Harborage. Meet us there.
What a mess. Apologies, Vanus, but I'm going to check on my Lion Guard.
I can still hear my heart beating. Am I alive? What should I do?
Where is everyone? I can hear wails and screams, but I can't see anyone! I need to get out of here!
Watch yourselves, outsiders. Give us a good reason, and the Armigers will cut you down where you stand!
We'll burn you â€¦.
Freeze you â€¦.
What was that? Something touched me! Mauloch, help me! I think I'm going insane!
And shatter you.
Any questions? I didn't think so.
Honored Skald-King, I am here with the personal champion of Queen Ayrenn â€¦.
Honored Skald-King, I am here with the personal champion of High King Emeric â€¦.
You dare to bring a Dominion lapdog here?
You dare to bring a Covenant lapdog here?
Silence, Thrush! Master Galerion, please continue.
Dearest? Brena? Can you hear me? I think something happened. Are you all right, my dearest?
Just rest easy, my love. I'm sure you will be fine. I feel so strange. So â€¦ confused. But don't worry, my dearest. Everything will be fine.
My companion hopes to speak with you about the impending Coldharbour crisis.
I have heard tales of this one. The Skald-King favors the bold, even among his enemies! Come, champion. Let us speak.
Thanks again, my friend. Stendarr defend you.
We rise to fight beside you!
Help us protect the roots!
Invaders! Cut them down!
We rise again. But for how long?
Hurry, to the gate!
Here we are. Watch your step as you descend.
Enemies at the inner gate! Come quickly, we'll drive out the Worm Cult!
How dare you intrude within my â€¦. What? It's you!
What's happened here? Where is Gilraen?nnSpread out and search for her.
Now, a toast! To finding my true form at last!
No! The tail is right, but why so many scales? My family will never accept me like this.
Montclair has gone mad! Does he really think he can win a civil war?
I'm as surprised as you are. I always thought Baron Montclair was a good man.
Well, I just hope we can resolve this before High King Emeric arrives.
Tread lightly. Few living have been permitted to walk among these honored dead.

Divad Hunding, son of Frandar do Hunding Hel Ansei No Shira, the greatest of the Sword Saints. The hearth of every household in Hammerfell has small alcove containing a copy of his father's greatest work, The Book of Circles.

Ra Abah was a warrior of great renown. He fought alongide Frandar Hunding in the seven great battles against the Armies of Hira, and survived. At the final battle at Hattu Mountain, more than three hundred thousand gave their lives.
Ansei Kalam, master of polearms, and his daughter Ra Adia. They swept through these mountain passes like a tempest, driving out the bandit tribes that had harrassed our people for two decades.
The twins of sword and spear, Ra Hasa and Ra Huzar, and their mother, Ansei Satameh the Tigress of Dragonstar.
It seems fitting that the Ring of Stendarr's Mercy lies with my father's greatsword. We will need both for the battles that lay before us.
It's just you and me now.
I had hoped otherwise, but I suppose it was always going to end this way. For all of us.

If only you had realized that before you let your undead children bury half the city down here. If your vanity had allowed you to alert the guards thisâ€”nnI don't suppose that matters very much to you. Let's get on with this.
Tell the lovely Copper Dariah that this one looks forward to seeing her lithe figure in her tight leathers.
Tell the lovely Dunmer, Naryu, that she is very welcome to disguise herself as a serving girl and show off for this one.
Raz! Inappropriate.
This one has no regrets.
That's old Dethin Halde's skull. As fine a man as ever lived, but he's no scholar.
Nothing! I'm trying to help!
Once again you bring us suffering. Banishment is too good for you, this time.
How touching! Your friends are here to save you. Pity they arrived too late. It's time for your next round of torture. You'll enjoy this one.
And darkness falls. This only gets better as we go along.
begins to shake.
Sai, my love. Where is the Amulet? If you tell me, this will all be over and we can finally be together.
That sounded like my voice! What's going on? I never said that!
You are not my love! Lyris would never torment me like this! Begone, foul temptress!
Arkay, lord of the seasons, please forgive my children their trespasses, and forgive me mine for refusing to allow their departure from this world.
It's done. Too late, but it's done.
Intruders! They're after the amulet! Don't worry, my love. My sisters will deal with these pests.
I knew I'd find them here! Interesting. I've never been to this area before but it's â€¦ breathtaking!
All right, the Countess has given us our orders! Let's head west and see if there's any truth to those disturbing rumors!
I'll deal with them. You'll be safe here, my love.
Greatly Esteemed Queen Ayrenn Arana Aldmeri, it is my great honor to present to you â€¦.

Vanus, you're so formal! I remember the patience and kindness you showed an awkward, freckled waif all those years ago on fair Summerset! You captured this child's heart then, and it remains with you to this day.
You warm an old man's heart, my Queen. I remember well those halcyon days.
As do I, my old friend. Sorry about all these guards. I'm told they're necessary. These are dark days.
A wise precaution, my Queen. My counsel would be no different. If you'll permit it, my companion would like to speak with you.
Ah yes. Let me meet this hero I've heard so much about. It's not often the heroic deeds of one who, by all rights, should be considered a mortal enemy, reach my ears. Come, let's talk.
Be thankful my hand was stayed. You deserve to die down here next to your children. Yahyif and I risked our lives to come down here to save your noble hide.
Too late, once again. Come, my pet. Time for your next session!
That's the last of them! We have all the pieces. We should go to the Constellation Room and put <<1>> back to sleep!
I'm not giving you a choice. Now move.
Please, just end this. I don't want to live.
You dare interrupt me? <<1>>, my son â€¦ see to this intruder!
Give my best to Thrush. Tell him I hope we can dance again, soon.
I thought you said this bastard wouldn't be able to speak.
He shouldn't be able to achieve coherent thought. We'll have to watch him carefully.
No! It hurts, it hurts!
Where is the Amulet of Kings? This can all be over if you just tell me. You can finally rest. You'd like that, wouldn't you, Sai?
Have I been here two years, or two thousand years? I can no longer tell. But I will never break! Never!
This one will meet you at the barn. Try not to get killed along the way.
Sai is in pain. Release his bonds, quickly!
You're sense of direction is impecable, that's the wrong way.
Protect the leaders! Defeat Molag Bal's minions and close the unstable rifts!
Peace at last.
The weapon is ready, comrade. Take it from the anvil, and follow us into battle!
Ah-hah! That's it. It's in the well water.
You have done it, Vestige! Bring him through the portal, quickly!
I won't let you kill him, Andur!
Stop Thief! I shall kill you where you stand!
Yes! This one knew the stone was the key!
Calm down, shaveskin. Your courage is commendable, but highly misplaced. We are here to help.
Leave this place! I won't let you wake him!
Stay back, vampire! I'll stick you with this sword. I mean it!
Stop acting like a coward, Dathieu! I am your king and I will lead you to victory today.
Your Majesty, you've clearly lost your mind. I'm sorry, but you leave me no choice.
It is done. No further lives need be thrown away today.
Traitor! But your feeble betrayal won't stop Reezal-Jul's magic! We shall live forever, but not you. I curse you and will scatter your bones! Die, you treacherous dog!
You killed Sees-All-Colors.
You saved Sees-All-Colors.
I'll never get used to this place. Come here, Vestige. I'd like a word before we skip off merrily to our doom.
Molag Bal will undoubtedly set his most powerful servants in our path. Prepare for the worst.
This place is alive with pain and suffering. This must be where Molag Bal torments those who displease him.
Look there! Is that Mannimarco?
Mannimarco! He was a back-stabbing hypocrite with delusions of godhood. The fool got precisely what he deserved!
Are you insane? That worm didn't deserve your mercy!
Ha! Sorry, trollsâ€”no dessert today!
Thanks barrels! Meet me on the Evermore Docks and I'll have your reward!
You actually released me? Naive fool! Future generations will pay for your weakness!
Molag Bal is here. I can feel his presence. Sense his foul breath upon the wind.
Cowards, the lot of you! This mine belongs to House Selos. You are intruders, and will be disciplined as such!
Go away! Leave us alone! I don't want to become a bloodfiend!
Gabrielle, focus all your energy into this! We can't let up!
I'm â€¦ doing â€¦ my â€¦ best!
These are some ugly bastards! Is this the best Molag Bal can throw at us? I'm hardly working up a sweat!
This may well be our last battle. Let's make them remember it!
You must hurry! My shield can't withstand much more of this!
Almost â€¦ there!
I can feel it, Vanus! We can beat this! We canâ€”Darien, behind you!
Have no fear, beautiful Gabrielle! I have this under control!
You have to hurry! We can't hold them back much longer.
Darien! Get back here! Darien!
Help! Don't let him take me!
That's the wrong way! There might be more of those things that way! I'm going back to my house.
No! What are you â€¦ what â€¦.
Rejoice! Soon we will have a new member of our family - Draven!
Patience, friends. I will speak to each of you individually.
I don't recognize you. Come, let us speak.
That carcass is mine! You won't leave here alive!
All right, let me see what components I have left. I should be able to cobble something together to slow a giant monster down â€¦.
What about that exploding squirrel you built when we were children? Or do you think that'd be too much?
Great Akatosh, Dragon God of Time, forgive me for my hubris. Grant your divine power to the Vestige and restore your protection to Tamriel, that my sacrifice might not be in vain.
Death is simply life's next great adventure, and I am prepared to make the journey. I hope to see you all again one day, in Sovngarde. Until then, it has been my greatest honor.
I am honored to make this sacrifice. When you think of me, I hope you remember me fondly, and sing songs of this day while you toast to my memory.
History may not remember your sacrifice, but those present here will never forget it.
Divines of Tamriel! With this vessel of your power, the Amulet of Kings, I call upon your strength!
Let this noble sacrifice be a testament to our desire to set things right and restore balance to the Mundus!
Your champion stands ready! Accept this offering and imbue this vestige with your glory! Let the will of Molag Bal be denied!
target: Il tuo campione Ã¨ pronto! Accetta questa offerta e imbevi questo vestigio della tua gloria! Fa che il volere di Molag Bal sia negato!

source: You there, wet one. This one needs to speak to you.
You won't believe who escaped from the Lightless Oubliette!
Someone actually got out of that place? Who was it?
Dynar, the last Ayleid King. I saw him ordering around the Fighters Guild.
New trinkets, but the box has not been opened. The time for gifts has not yet come.
Molag Bal tried to pull Nirn into Coldharbour, but thankfully his plans were foiled.
The Great Shackle? Whoever it was, they must have been exceedingly brave to defy Molag Bal of his greatest invention.
I heard someone destroyed the Great Shackle.
That was fun, but the main assault needs me now. Don't get yourself killed while I'm gone.
We have spilled much blood, but now your army calls for my aid. Perhaps we shall see each other again if the Great Egg wills it.
Alas, fine friend, the Fighters Guild has need of me. Do stay out of trouble while I'm gone.
When the truth is silenced, it is the people who are shackled.
Sind!
Tand! You're alive!
I thought I'd never see you again.
What? How did you get down here?
Come here.
Please, no lecture! This one is sorry.
You deserve one. We were worried about you!
Tand knows.
Life is a story, yes? We must live through it together. You cannot skip to the last page, win a life in a gambling den.
Tand knows, he just â€¦ wanted to make you and Muzag proud.
We are proud of you! Your father, your sister, me. You do not need a lot of coin to make us proud.
Tand knows!
We're here for you. You know that. We'll get through this. This is nothing like the time with those Colovians, yeah? The time you almost lost your eye?
Heh, that was a bad one. This one loves you, Sind.
I love you too, Tand.
<<1>>, a moment? This recruit survived the shipwreck without injuries. You mentioned something about <<Ac:2>>, yes?
Very good, <<1>>. I'll take it from here.
<<1>> is this way.
<<1>>, this recruit wishes to speak with you.
We should speak privately. Before you depart, let's meet by the statues north of camp.
Would you look at it go! Hmm? Yes, wonderful, put them on the workbench.
Who dares to defy the Dutchess of Anguish? I will tear out your heart and make you feast upon it!
What death do you prefer, mortal? Slow and painful, or quick and painful?
Here are the <<mz:1>>. A little dusty, but they'll do.
I think I'll kill you quickly, then resurrect you and kill you slowlyâ€”an eternity of agony. It will be glorious.
Aieeeee!
Quite simple to use. Point it at the Daedra you want to absorb and the <<z:1>> does the rest.
Vampire or bloodfiend, you will fall to Adusa's terribly swift blades! Oh, it's just you. Never mind, then.
This doesn't look like a safe place. I'm going back into hiding!
I don't think so.
What in Oblivion? What is this? Release me, at once! Release me, or I'll tear this plane apart!
Ignore it. Just empty threats. It knows it's trapped.
You insufferable mortals! I'll shroud you all in unending dream, make you face your worst nightmares! You'll die clawing your eyes out, I swear it!
It's losing the fight. The stone just needs to hold a little bit longer.
I have plenty of time to wait, mortal. Eventually, you'll slip, and your prison will fail. Then I will cover you in nightmares.
Draven! What's going on? No one will tell me a thing!
Come and sit, dear. Everything will be all right.
I can't be the only one who thinks something strange is going on!
Kerbol and the lot of them! They're some kind of cult!
Renoit â€¦ let it rest. Soon I'll be betterâ€”doesn't that count for something?
Yes, that's it! <<AC:1>> thirsts for souls!
And if I twist, just so â€¦.
The power! I'd forgotten how it feels!
Follow, outsider. Come see my Prince's glorious domain!
You won't leave here alive!
Look what happened! They came out of nowhere. Captain Janeve is missing, half the refugees are dead. Healer Odylie is doing what she can to help.
What've you done to my husband?
I think he heard me. He should manifest right here.
I'll see you back in Thormar, dearie.
No! You won't defeat me again!
You've nowhere to fly, fiend! You can't escape me!
<<1>>! You live?
Yes, <<1>>. Despite your efforts!
My Prince's children were legion! They should have overwhelmed you!
Molag Bal's chattel are nothing to me.
Blasphemy!
Stranger! If you're a foe to Molag Bal, stand with me!
Fools! I'll feast upon your eyes!
Ugh. Disgusting.
There's no turning back now, Draven. You are a part of this village now.
I'll let you handle this one. I'll take the next.
We showed them!
Don't be alarmed. Soon the pain will subside.
No â€¦ stop! You're in my head!
Don't interrupt the ritual!
Divines protect me!
Are they gone? I thought you were going to take me to the barn.
We'll do this together, then. You fight them head-on. I'll strike from the shadows.
Ah, the good ol' library! Read many of the books here myself. I love the ones with all the pictures in them.
Feast, my children! Feast on bones and blood!
This might hurt a bit.
No! No more blood! No more!
No! I've lost control!
Draven! Come back!
Everyone, stay calm!
We will soon have this back in hand. Keep faith, my friends.
Renoit, bring Draven to the town hall. Stranger, come with me.
Please, don't leave yet. Can I talk to you?
Draven? What's happened!
Vestige! Meet me at the Harborage! We are ready to reclaim the Amulet of Kings!
You're not far now. Through the door, and to the summit!
Filthy Ra Gada! I'll pick my teeth with your bones!
Stupid Redguard! You served your purpose. Now you will die!
You are not welcome here! We will defend our land!
You are not welcome here! We will defend our land!
This must be what we're looking for. Amazing. It's as though it has been waiting for us all of this time.
No! How dare you, mortal?
I am the Artificer, madam! That's why I dare!
I'm staying here.
Can you feel it? That energy in the air! The spell is working!
You could have hidden that amulet anywhere in Tamriel, and this was your first choice?
It seemed like a good idea at the time.
Those shades â€¦ they were going to kill me!
Thank you! I can make it back to camp from here.
That is indeed an immense relief, Hjurrun. Gives us room to breathe. But it doesn't mean we can rest on our laurels.
I know. It's only one victory, Your Grace, but I hope it's a sign of more to come.
I do too, but that's going to require more work on both our parts, and there's nothing for it but to get it done. You're dismissed, Captain.
At last. After all these years â€¦.
I don't want to die!
That was an impressive show of combat prowess, stranger!
I'm not comfortable following you out there. I'll just go back to my favorite hiding spot now.
What have you done?
Ah, there you are. Come, we must talk.
Hmmmmmmmâ€¦
Lyris? Is this true, child?
You were always so cold. So distant. My mother died giving me life. It was my fault! I should never have been born!

Lyris, look at me. The blood of giants flows through my veins. Your mother was a Nord. I gave her my seed without thought for her safety. That's why she died. Not because of you, child. Because of me!
DEPRECATE

DEPRECATEnnYou wanted to fight injustice. To see the world. I was afraid to let go, though I knew I must. Look at you now. You're a fine woman and a noble warrior. You will do great things. I didn't often say it, but I've always loved you.
I thought you blamed me. You â€¦ you couldn't even look at me, Papa!

Do you not see? When I looked at you, I saw her face. I loved her, child. Just as I love youâ€”more than life itself. We cannot change the past, nor should we cling to it. You must not let these feelings haunt you. Let them go. Let me go.
I love you too, Papa. Rest now. Be at peace.
He's gone. Come on, let's get out of here.
No! You can't!
Well done! Now we can deal with the barrier.
Go forth and destroy the barrier!
After a careful review of the evidence provided to this court â€¦.
That was unpleasant.
Do you hear that? Like a scratching sound? Something's coming!
I find Aranak the merchant guilty as charged.
We find the evidence presented inadequate to prove the guilt of Aranak the merchant.
Advocate, we have asked much of you in this terrible affair, but I must rely upon you for one final sacred task. Please escort the prisoner to the judgment chamber below.
Advocate, please return once you have reviewed your findings and are ready to present us with a different set of evidence.
The barrier has fallen! Move out!
Oh no!
We have to get out of here!
The lever to open the gate is in that crypt ahead. It should be easy to - watch out!
Vestige! Go into the crypt and open the gate! We'll stay up here in case any more gargoyles appear.
Vestige! We have visitors!
The streets are dangerous. We should check the homes. Be neighborly. See if those inside know where the scouts are.
I'm sorry. I never meant to bring this on the village.
Get away from that gate, you fools! It's a trap!
Is that â€¦ ? Shor's bones, it is! Vestige, that's my battle axe!
Mannimarco? How did you find this place?
Get out of here! Follow Tharayyaâ€”I'll cover your escape!
Do you really think I'd allow you to escape the Halls of Torment if I couldn't track your every movement?
Sai, no! Mannimarco, stop! You're killing him!
Where is the Amulet of Kings?  My master, Molag Bal, demands it!
Your master. Please! You would use the amulet to betray Molag Bal!
Fools! What are you doing out there?
I'm getting out of here. I recommend you do the same.
This mayor seems a charming fellow. We should decide what must be done about him.
Can you feel her suffering, her agony?
For a thousand years her pain tunneled through the void, always reaching for her last memories of a life free of suffering.
No more!
Come. We end this today.
Persistent, aren't you? Do you really think you can keep me from acquiring the amulet?
The Amulet of Kings is under the protection of Stendarr's ward! It will never be yours!
The Aedra? They are absent parents for this forsaken world. Do you think they really care about you?
You're insane if you think you can betray the God of Schemes!
I find Spinner Eranas guilty as charged.
I find the Spinner's wife Gathiel guilty as charged.
This island belongs to the Maormer!
They can't be allowed to interfere. Eliminate them!
We find the evidence presented inadequate to prove the guilt of Spinner Eranas.
We find the evidence presented inadequate to prove the guilt of Gathiel, the Spinner's Wife.
You've destroyed one anchor out of dozens! Pathetic fools!
We're finished here. Let's keep moving.
So be it.
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry. I just â€¦ I was afraid to die.
Please. A moment, my friends. I â€¦ I must rest before we continue.
Sai? Are you all right? That bastard really hurt you, didn't he? I swear to the gods I'll take his head off!
I'll be fine, Snow Lily. I just need a moment to catch my breath.
That wasn't so difficult, was it? Now, let's head to my laboratory. We'll need that scroll to get into the cathedral.
Who are you?
There! I helped! Mother always says I should help others. Just squeeze through there!
No, please! I don't want to stay here!
It's no use! Get out of there or the lightning will destroy you!
Wait a moment! You shouldn't do this alone.
Verandis says you're too valuable to die in here. But you're in luckâ€”he sent me.
Take the orc and get her back to the surface. I'll make sure things are taken care of down here.
My pet! I'll tear your throat out for that.
Shatter the <<mz:1>>! They shackle <<2>> to this wretched place!
And how am I supposed to trust you?
This one could have overpowered you at any time. Now stand down or Adusa will stick that sword where the Bright Moons never shine.
Pleaseâ€”I need you to kill me.
What? How dare you! Oh, very well! I'll just go and sit down or something.
Another projection. Let's follow it.
I'm free!
Didn't think you had it in you! But the storm's clearing. We should head to my laboratory.
Ha! I'm sorry, I just â€¦ I wasn't expecting that. We should head to my laboratory, now that the storm's clearing and all.
It is done.
Tell Kerbol we've got another one.
What is it that Varen calls you? Vestige? Let's see how special you are without the help of your friends.
Now where did she â€¦ ah, yes! It's on my desk. Yes, over there, do you see it?
Didn't I make myself clear? You better be bringing me Adusa's head or news from Lleraya or so help me I'll turn you into a Bloodfiend myself.
Let's head to the cathedral. We're the last people the mayor will expect!
(incomprehensible chanting)
Blood for blood.
If you have a moment, I would appreciate a word.
â€¦ thank you â€¦.
The portal is open! Go, now. Return with the Amulet of Kings!
I didn't survive the terrors of Crestshade just to die out here in the middle of nowhere!
Monsters, they attacked the camp. I'm leaving, but if you plan to linger here, you should talk to Healer Odylie. Good luck to you!
I've a surprise for you, Sai. Do you remember your fallen comrades from the Dragonguard? I've taken the liberty of raising them, and they're quite anxious to see you.
No! You will not take my grandchildren from me!
You aren't who I was expecting. Good. I didn't really want to kill Adusa just yet. You, on the other hand? I will enjoy feasting on your blood!
Clothes are fine. The poison wasn't in the stream.
Hmm. The meat is cooked past the point of edibility, but no poison.
If it's not the well water, we'll need to rethink this.
Wait, do you smell that?
I never wanted Yahyif to die.
I know what you're trying to do. Now shut it.
He was your best friend.
I said shut it!
Is that the mayor? Wait, I recognize him! Let me see if I can talk some sense into him.
Your cargo's unloaded and I'm here for my payment. I hope you don't come to regret this, Hjurrun.
If I come to regret this, I'll probably be dead anyways. I don't expect you to understand, Captain. Here's your payment.
Thanks. When are you and your "allies" making your move? I want to make sure I'm long gone by then.
We're arming everyone up at the weapons cache in the south alley in just a few hours, so I'd set sail right away. Kyne speed you, Captain.
Help! Pleaseâ€¦ we need help here.
The shrine is on the far side of the room. Quickly, we must find our way across!
Again, the King of Worms defiles the memory of the honored dead! I have no wish to disfigure the corpses of my old comrades of the Dragonguard, but we must consecrate the shrine.
Who's there? How did you get in? Go, I want to be alone!
Don't you recognize me, <<1>>?
<<1>>! Thank the Divines. <<2>> did this, all of it. He used me!
And how exactly did he use you?
He promised me power, the respect I deserve â€¦ but then he cursed my tongue with madness and let me make a mess of this town!
You're so pitiful, even for a mortal.
What?
adwd
You heard me!
I've always wanted to meet a person within a person! Tell me, what's it like?
Take all the time you need. I'll keep watch. If there's anything I can do, just name it.
I was afraid you were going to say that.
Don't speak so soon. There's no telling what's lying in wait for us here.
The altar is on the far side, but to reach it, the drawbridge must be lowered.
You did it! The bridge is down!
You really are starting to annoy me. Kill them!
Are we ready to finish this, old friend?
We have only to get the Amulet. Take your crystal and place it in the receptacle, on my mark.
Place the crystal now, Lyris!
The crystals are in place. Use the ring to open the door!
I've always wanted to meet a person within a person! Tell me, what's it like?
I'm â€¦ I'm so sorry, Sheo! You've always left a note. I thought you'd abandoned me!

Get on your knees and tell me your sorry and maybe I will forgive you. I've taken aliking to my recent companion and I'm thinking of letting them chop your head off, if they are so inclined, of course.
I'm â€¦ I'm so sorry, <<1>>! I thought you'd abandoned me!
Aulie, I left you a tongue that drives people mad! But I suppose if you don't want my gift, I can take it from your mouth and give it to my new favorite mortal friend.
No! Think of all I've built here, the wonderful screams I've created, all in your name. Doesn't that make me your favorite?
Oh, very well. Sorry, my second favorite mortal friend! We had a good run, but it's time for your curtain call.
What a foul sensation!
I'm sure we'll meet again, you and I.
If you're headed to Crestshade, you need to know. There was trouble there.
Be careful in there. I need to get to Shornhelm and give my report.
Apologies for my lateness.
Good! Now the other!
That's it! Quickly, free <<1>> from the altar!
Her bones are free! Quickly, recover them!
I've heard enough! I'll be outside.
You, outsider! Bandits broke into the village!
Look, it's Lady Laurent!
Wonderful. It's Telenger.
The captain in charge of security, Alphaury, is over there.
The vault is just past this room. We're almost there.
Good, you're finally coming out of it. We should â€¦ reintroduce ourselves.
Look out! Another anchor!
I swear by Stendarr's grace and the sword of my father, you will not win, Mannimarco!
Your pathetic efforts will not succeed! The Amulet of Kings will be mine!
Through the power of the Amulet of Kings, I will be transformed!
Champion. It is time. You are at the end of your path.
The vault door is open! Let's go!
As the Lunar Champion, you have proven yourself time and time again a leader of our people, but do you truly understand what it means to be the Mane?
Yes. I've walked the path and know what lies ahead and honor those left behind.
As the Lunar Champion, you have proven yourself time and time again a leader of our people, but do you truly understand what it means to be the Mane?
You've begun the path and know what lies ahead of our people. Are you prepared to lead your people?
Yes, I accept this role in service of kith and kin.
Then wear this as leader of our people and rise, Mane of our people.
Continue the path, young one, and accept this blessing for the journey ahead.
Rejoice one and all! Long live the Mane!
Draven, wait!
We can't go through the town. Not after what's happened.
Renchant, you bastard â€¦ I rue the day I gave you the throne. What you've done â€¦ is nothing less than treason.
Guard! Come get this coward out of my sight!
Such despair! Richer than a cheese sorbet!
Yes, Your Majesty. As you wish.
I'll come quietly, Guardsman.
Now that he's been dealt with, we have real work to do. Please, meet me outside.
<<1>> is near those glowing stones. Be careful!
The time has come to demonstrate the true power of my kind. We are not simply monsters who eat children! We are so much more.
One last quest, old chap! One last leap into the fire! Unless we survive, of course. But how likely is that?
You've come through these trials and emerged victorious.
And make it entertaining, would you? After spending so much time in this town, I finally know where the Colovians keep their fur hats.
I know I can activate the Welkynd Stones. Let's see what happens.
Bridge is out! My boredom washed it away. Really got in the cracks, there!
Well, well. It appears you're not so special after all!
Very well then. Arzhela, my fate is in your hands. You know I made the only rational choice.
I was wondering when you were going to arrive, Adusa.
I wouldn't call it rational, Renchant. I would call it cowardly. Eamond died defending this kingdom â€¦ and you'll die for betraying it.
Mara's bosom, Bugbekh! What do you plan on burying out here? A mammoth?
It was for King Eamond - but then I hear that they carted his body south to Bangkorai Garrison.
I had no idea the King was that fat.
Watch your tongue you lout. Our king was a good and honest man. It's a tragedy what happened to him.
Yes, yes, whatever you say. You never did answer my question though. What is this hole for?
Well we can't bury the king here so we got the next best thing.
If only I could turn back time â€¦ just a few hours â€¦.
What's that?
His horse â€¦. Mauloch's jawbone, I've got a lot of work to do.
Medya, what is it? Is Sir Etienne all right?
I had to dig three more crows out of my chimney flue this morning. We may have suffocated if not for the dog barking.
Believe me, I can empathize. I've found bird droppings in my porridge twice in the last week.
I've never seen the like. What could be causing it?
Witchcraft I should think. Or maybe something with the weather. Who knowsâ€”I'm hardly a scholar.
Well I'm off to Shara's shop to buy a bow and arrow.
Are you sure that's wise? If there truly is a hex on this town, I'd give those crows a wide berth.
Perhaps you're right. Maybe I'll just buy a cat and see what happens.
Do what you want. I have nothing left to live for.
Hey you, please wait!
Here she comes now â€¦. Rashan. We have a volunteer to destroy Uela's totems.
I don't understand why you're so upset, darling. It's not like they need their valuables any more.
Those are our dearly departed! Because of you, our dead ancestors are trying to kill us!
This isn't my fault. You returned the cursed heirlooms, but your dear papa is still trying to kill us. Clearly, these two things aren't the least bit related.
Why do I get the feeling we're going to regret this?
This is your chance to fix this mess. Go, deal with the "mayor." If <<1>> bores him, <<2>> will leave.
There. That place should serve us well. Let us assemble and prepare the ritual.
It would be my pleasure!
Kill this worm.
Abnur, why don't you show this puppet, magic's true potential?
This just isn't your day. But your Uncle <<1>> can make it better!
Greetings, vestige. Although, perhaps that term no longer applies. Come â€” we must talk.
target: Saluti, spirito. Anche se, forse ora questa nomÃ¬a non Ã¨ piÃ¹ idonea. Vieni - dobbiamo parlare.

source: What is this?
This has got to be the source of the spell. Let's destroy it!
Wait a moment. Let's regroup before we move on.
Free Will! Get out here, there's someone I want you to meet!
Toodles!
Ah, I found you at last! Come out of there so we can talk.
Renoit! Stay back!
Look what we have here.
Quiet â€¦ I think I hear something.
What is this?
It's time you paid for what you did to our world.
He's doing fine. And when he returns, you all will leave?
We'll stay until Murcien's Hamlet is free, or Sir Etienne and I both fall in the fight.
I see. Well, he'll be resting comfortably soon, don't you fret.
Sai Sahan! Intruders â€¦ cultists â€¦ they attacked the abbey. So many of my students have fallen â€¦.
It's Draven! It's got to be! Come on!
The abbey is in ruins, Kasura! How could they â€¦?
Let's go. There's nothing left for us in this town.
A gigantic beast â€¦ like nothing I've ever seen! The cultists â€¦ they're opening rifts to Oblivion!
Save your strength, Kasura. We will make them pay, I promise you!
Draven? Oh, you're â€¦ back to a werewolf.
You'll pay for this, Kerbol!
Draven is no more. He's an animal, only fit to be put down!
Save our village! Strike down the beast!
I'll go see to the poor knight now, then.
This looks like the place. I guess you're the one who's going in.
He's gone. I can only hope he'll be all right.
Foul troll. Begone!
I'm sorry, Renoit. Gods be with you.
No! What've you done?
Aha! More knucklebones for my necklace!
Remember, with gusto! A big steaming pile of it!
There. Back in the physical realm. Time to do this.
Good. Good, he's all right. Now, let's go over what we need.
All right! The door should be open now! Go get me that heart!
He's locked the door!
There must be some way to unlock it. Check around the altars.
Stand back from the door. This will take but a moment.
Confound that beast. Let's get moving! Looks like someone opened the door ahead.
It is done.
What do you mean, coming to kill me?
It's a gift! A chance to shine, to prove you have some backbone that won't snap at the lightest touch! Really, Aulie, I'm quite fond of you. Mmm. Fondue. What was I saying?
That you're fond of me. That you don't want to watch me die!
Watch you die horribly, all alone, and laughing my head off when it happens? That doesn't sound like me. Does it? But I'm sure you can work the matter out for yourself.
Good! Looks like everyone ended up in the right place. Let's get to our positions.
Please, don't do this! Maybe we can work something out?
There it is! The Amulet of Kings!
You're too late, old friend. This place is already slipping into Coldharbour. The Amulet of Kings is mine!
Show yourself, worm! Face us! Or are you a coward?
How can I refuse such a humble request? The Amulet of Kings is mine! I am the new God of Schemes! And yours will be the first soul I tear apart!
My friend tells me something's stirred up the Wood Orcs again.
Gods, I need help! My liege, no!
Pah! This one has had enough of Wood Orcs for a lifetime.
The Bramblebreach clan is under constant attack, lately.
No doubt the Dominion will offer their help, in exchange for an alliance. Turning the misfortunes of others to their advantage. That is their way.
I hear that someone drove the Wood Orcs away from Bramblebreach.
This one heard the same. Heard they ran away like cowards.
All except for their War Captain. He stayed and fought.
It's good for the Bramblebreach, but this one wonders how long their isolationist ways can last. Wood Orcs aren't the only threats in Valenwood.
I heard an interesting story the other day.
Not another of your stories.
The Wood Elves deep in the forest say there's a being called the Wilderking who shapes Valenwood.
Sounds like a load of superstition to me.
Strange happenings in the Court of the Wilderking. Did you hear?
More Wilderking nonsense.
No nonsense. This is real. They say an Altmer girl saved his life, and then took his place.
You are too gullible, friend.
I'd tell you how your sister was doing if I could.
Something's wrong. I know it! What aren't you telling me?
The Maulborn are here to help, my friend. I'm sure your sister is being well cared for. I'm sorry, I can't tell you anything else.
